<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">

<h5><a href="present.htm">På svenska tack</a></h5>

<p><font size="5"><strong>About Peter Curman</strong></font></p>

<p><font size="3">Born in Stockholm in 1941. Author and
journalist. A-levels in 1962. Paper on Finno-Swedish modernist
author Henry Parland while at university. Travel guide in Rhodes
1963-1966. Début in 1965 with poetry collection OBS! Viktigt!
(N.B! Important!). In the same year C, in conjunction with
Ingemar Lindahl, published &quot;På eget sätt&quot;, a
collection of John Lennon's nonsense verse. C, together with the
authors Gösta Friberg and Siv Arb, in 1967 initiated The
Author's Centre, contact point for Swedish authors. Joint editor
1970-1971 of the socio-political magazine &quot;R&quot;.
1981-1983 head of the culture section of Stockholm morning daily
Stockholms-Tidningen. 1983-1986 head of culture section of
evening daily Aftonbladet. 1987-1996 chairman of Swedish Author's
Union. Initiator of &quot;Waves of the Baltic Sea&quot; in 1992,
which resulted in the creation of The Baltic Writer's and
Translator's Centre on the island of Gotland, and of the Black
Sea Cruise &quot;Waves of the Black Sea&quot; resulting in the
recently inaugurated International Writers' and Translator's
Centre of Rhodes. 1995 chairman of KLYS, the Swedish Joint
Committee for Artistic and Literary Professionals. 1993 chairman
of the committee for cultural exchange between Sweden and Greece,
a section of the National Council for Cultural Affairs.</font></p>

<p><font size="4"><strong>Books:</strong></font></p>

<ul>
    <li><a href="titlar/obs-viktigt.htm"><font size="3">OBS!
        Viktigt! poems 1965</font></a><font size="3">. På eget
        sätt, translation of John Lennon's &quot;In his own
        write&quot; (with Ingemar Lindahl)</font></li>
    <li><font size="3">Kretsloppa, poems 1966</font></li>
    <li><font size="3">Skolhat, anthology 1966</font></li>
    <li><font size="3">Genom nålsögat, poems 1967</font></li>
    <li><font size="3">13 interner: Vår fångvård, anthology
        1968</font></li>
    <li><a href="titlar/hemmaliv.htm"><font size="3">Hemmaliv,
        dikter 1970</font></a></li>
    <li><a href="titlar/fonstren.htm"><font size="3">Fönstren,
        dikter 197</font></a><font size="3">2</font></li>
    <li><a href="titlar/vanddigom.htm"><font size="3">Vänd dig
        om och ta emot mig, dikter 1977</font></a></li>
    <li><font size="3">Fåglarna, dikter 1977</font></li>
    <li><font size="3">Ännu spinner tiden, dikter 1979</font></li>
    <li><a href="titlar/fodelsemarken.htm"><font size="3">Födelsemärken,
        dikter 1981</font></a></li>
    <li><font size="3">Barnens maskerad, dikter 1986 (in the
        anthology Fotspår, 1986)</font></li>
    <li><font size="3">Waves of the Baltic Sea, seapoem 1 (with
        Ewa A. Kumlien)</font></li>
    <li><font size="3">Waves of the Black Sea, seapoem 2 (with
        Ewa A. Kumlien)</font></li>
    <li><font size="3">Ställ aldrig om hjärtat, poems 1995.</font></li>
</ul>

