<html>

<head>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type"
content="text/html; charset=iso-8859-1">
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 2.0">
<title>Peter Curman - Print-on-demand</title>
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 2.0">
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">

<h5><a href="present.htm">På svenska tack</a></h5>

<p><font size="5"><strong>Print-on-demand</strong></font></p>

<p><font size="3">Sweden's book trade treat books like
perishables. Even if it took the author years to write his book,
its shelf life in the bookshop is limited to maybe six months,
whereafter it is mercilessly thrown out. It's kept in stock for a
while, then included in the annual bargain sale. It's not old
books that are offered in todays bargain sales, but new ones -
which then simply disappear. This part of our national heritage
can then only be found in our libraries. </font></p>

<p><font size="3">The Swedish bookselling business is the most
unregulated in Europe, perhaps in the entire world. Ever since
the system of fixed book prices was abandoned in 1970, the
various parties of the book business are at each others throats.
Book clubs and major stores wage battle against traditional book
stores; the publishers have terminated the authors' agreement
from 1947. Chaos reigns in the Swedish book market.</font></p>

<p><font size="3">Pending proposals in a forthcoming report from
the Ministry of Culture, we authors have to deal with these
problems on our own. </font></p>

<p><font size="3">Thanks to a cooperation with Arkitektkopia and
with the aid of new technology - Internet and Print-On-Demand -
it is now possible to offer out-of-print books in a new and
relatively cheap manner.</font></p>

<p><font size="3">Just fill in the </font><a
href="../print-on-demand/bokbestallning970114.htm"><font size="3">order
form</font></a><font size="3"> and press a button - and you'll
have a book in the mail in a matter of days!</font></p>

<p><font size="4"><strong>The following of my books are available
in this fashion:</strong></font></p>

<ul>
    <li><a href="titlar/obs-viktigt.htm"><font size="3"><em>OBS!
        Viktigt, poems, 1965</em></font></a></li>
    <li><a href="titlar/hemmaliv.htm"><font size="3"><em>Hemmaliv,
        poems 1970</em></font></a></li>
    <li><a href="titlar/fonstren.htm"><font size="3"><em>Fönstren,
        poems 1972</em></font></a></li>
    <li><a href="titlar/vanddigom.htm"><font size="3"><em>Vänd
        dig om och ta emot mig, poems 1975</em></font></a></li>
    <li><a href="titlar/fodelsemarken.htm"><font size="3"><em>Födelsemärken,
        poems 1981</em></font></a></li>
    <li><a href="titlar/ayakizleri.htm"><i>AYAK IZLERI (poems in
        turkish)</i></a></li>
</ul>

<p><font size="4"><strong>SPECIAL OFFER:</strong></font></p>

<p><a href="titlar/nuflygerjag.htm"><font size="4"><em><strong>Lotta
Strömberg: Nu flyger jag!</strong></em></font></a><font size="4"><em><strong>
(Look, I'm flying!)</strong></em></font></p>

<p><font size="3">This collection of &quot;women's rights
poetry&quot; by &quot;Lotta Strömberg&quot; (a nom de plume) is
now available for the the first time in book form. The poems were
written in connection with a television program scrutinizing
opportunistic trend policies adopted by today's publishers.
During the actual transmission of the program Mr. Stig Edling,
then publisher at Prisma, realized he was the subject of a
practical joke and turned down the collection. Thanks to
Print-On-Demand this book can now reach readers on wings of its
own.</font></p>

