<html>
<head>
<title>Internet and literature - session 2</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<p align="center"><font size="7">Internet and Literature</font><br>
<font size="5">News from the seminar 23 september 1996</font></p>
<hr>
<p><strong><img src="images/nicos.JPG" align="right" hspace="10"
width="90" height="155"></strong><font size="4"><strong>Nicholaos
Sandu</strong></font><strong><br>
</strong>from Romania, stressed the importance of Internet as a
means of communication. But, he remarked, there is still a lot of
practical problems waiting to be solved. He raised the topic of
accessibility to the Internet for authors, translators and the
general public in the eastern European countries. Mr Sandu hoped
that this seminar will adress this problem. </p>
<hr>
<p><img src="images/portrait2-s.JPG" align="left" hspace="10"
width="250" height="195"><font size="4"><strong>Novica Milic</strong></font><strong><br>
</strong>from the Belgrade Circle, started with a discussion of
computers - is it a typewriter or a way of communicating? Both,
of course. It's important to discover the possibilities this
technology provides. It's vital to ask &#147;What is computer
technology doing to the world? To ourselves?&#148; </p>
<p>During the war in Yugoslavia communication broke down. But
thanks to the Internet there was a possibility to uphold
communications between Belgrade, Zagreb and Sarajevo during the
war years. For two years this was the only way of passing
messages back and forth. It helped to establish contacts between
members of familys that were divided. </p>
<p>Internet itself was constructetd by the military to overcome
breakdowns in communicationlines between computers. &#147;So you
have to go beyond the cuts, and that's how Internet works.&#148;
During the war small networks of people with computers and access
to Internet were created. The principle is the same with the
Internet as a whole; there is not one single center, but several.
Networks exist on different levels, from the family and up, at
the workplace, nationwide and globally. It is crucial to connect
these networks to each other. </p>
<p><a name="Internetional">Novica Milic</a> told us about his
plans for the online-magazine InterNETional. The aim with this
project is to promote &#147;internetional&#148; contacts; to
create new kinds of virtual communities. </p>
<p>&#147;If we understand this technology, we can use it in a
more sensible way&#148;, he concluded.</p>
