<h1 align="center"><a name="Top"><font size="5"><b>Inauguration</b></font></a><font
size="5"><b> Programme of the<br>
</b></font><a href="wt-centre.htm"><font size="5"><b>International
Writers' and Translators' Centre of Rhodes</b></font></a><font
size="5"><b> <br>
Under the Auspices of UNESCO </b></font><a
href="http://www.unesco.org/" target="_Blank"><b><img
src="images/UNESCO.gif" align="bottom" border="0" width="497"
height="43"></b></a></h1>
<h1 align="center"><em><b>Programme</b></em><b>: September 23-27
1996<br>
</b><a href="sponsors.htm"><font size="2"><b>Our Sponsors</b></font></a></h1>
<h2 align="center"><a href="#MONDAY"><font size="2"><b>Monday 23</b></font></a><font
size="2"><b> | </b></font><a href="#TUESDAY"><font size="2"><b>Tuesday
24</b></font></a><font size="2"><b> | </b></font><a
href="#WEDNESDAY"><font size="2"><b>Wednesday 25</b></font></a><font
size="2"><b> | </b></font><a href="#THURSDAY"><font size="2"><b>Thursday
26</b></font></a><font size="2"><b> | </b></font><a
href="#FRIDAY"><font size="2"><b>Friday 27</b></font></a><font
size="2"><b> | </b></font><a href="#Top"><font size="2"><b>Top of
page</b></font></a></h2>
<hr>
<p>(for early arrivers with charters and ships we will arrange
informal gatherings, on <strong>Saturday September 21</strong>
and <strong>Sunday September 22</strong>. Meeting Place in the
Belvedere Hotel Lobby at 20.00 o&#146;clock both evenings for
welcoming and announcement of activities)</p>
<h2><a name="MONDAY"><b>MONDAY</b></a><b> SEPTEMBER 23</b> </h2>
<p><font size="4"><strong><i>10.00-18.30</i></strong></font><i><br>
SEMINAR ON LITERATURE AND INTERNET <br>
at Paradise Hotel </i></p>
<p><a href="http://193.13.13.22/seminar/seminar.htm"><strong><i>Report
from the seminar</i></strong></a></p>
<p><i>The idea of the Seminar is to link together the
participating countries on the net with literary homepages. We
need to get more information about the literary and cultural
lives of our respective countries and by creating such homepages
we could open new ways of contacts between writers, literary
magazins, publishers and others. As we also want to protect the
copyright of the writer in electronic publishing we have invited
experts in this field from various countries. We intend to give
direct report from the web-server of Rhodes for all those
interested that cannot be with us on the spot.<br>
We are thankful to our Norwegian sponsors Kopynor and the Swedish
Writers&#180;Fund.</i></p>
<p><strong><i>Chairman:</i></strong><i><br>
Costas Tsolakidis, from the Aegean University of Rhodes</i></p>
<p><strong><i>Organisers:</i></strong><i><br>
Bente Christensen, Peter Curman and Uwe Friesel of the Working
Committee</i></p>
<p><strong><i>Morning:</i></strong><i><br>
Technical possibilities and problems.<br>
Other speakers: H&aring;kan Norelius, Sweden and Mart Marend,
Gotland, Nicholaos Sandu, Romania, Novica Milic, Belgrade Circle,
Dimitrios Kilias, FORTHnet, Rhodes</i></p>
<p><strong><i>Afternoon:</i></strong><i><br>
Copyright issues / creativity / freedom of expression</i> <i>Gun
Magnusson - Copyswede, Sweden, Helge S&ouml;nneland - Ministry of
Culture, Norway, Mette Newt, Norway and others</i> </p>
<p><font size="4"><strong><i>22.00</i></strong></font><i><br>
Informal </i><a href="http://193.13.13.22/seminar/poetry.htm"><strong><i>poetry
reading</i></strong></a><i> at Sun Wing Hotel Amfi Theatre</i> </p>
<p align="center"><a href="#MONDAY"><font size="2"><b>Monday 23</b></font></a><font
size="2"><b> | </b></font><a href="#TUESDAY"><font size="2"><b>Tuesday
24</b></font></a><font size="2"><b> | </b></font><a
href="#WEDNESDAY"><font size="2"><b>Wednesday 25</b></font></a><font
size="2"><b> | </b></font><a href="#THURSDAY"><font size="2"><b>Thursday
26</b></font></a><font size="2"><b> | </b></font><a
href="#FRIDAY"><font size="2"><b>Friday 27</b></font></a><font
size="2"><b> | </b></font><a href="#Top"><font size="2"><b>Top of
page</b></font></a></p>
<h2><a name="TUESDAY"><b>TUESDAY</b></a><b> SEPTEMBER 24</b> </h2>
<p><font size="4"><strong><i>10.00 - 13.00</i></strong></font><i><br>
Open Meeting - &#147;Summing up and new Perspectives&#147;<br>
all participants invited (Uwe Friesel of the working committee,
moderator)</i> <i>at the Paradise Hotel</i>.</p>
<p align="left"><em><strong>Additional programme - special offer:</strong></em><em><br>
</em><font size="4"><em><strong>23.00</strong></em></font><em><br>
Comic Poetry reading by Canadian born poet Robert MacLean in a
local bar.</em></p>
<p align="center"><a href="#MONDAY"><font size="2"><b>Monday 23</b></font></a><font
size="2"><b> | </b></font><a href="#TUESDAY"><font size="2"><b>Tuesday
24</b></font></a><font size="2"><b> | </b></font><a
