size="2"><b> | </b></font><a href="#Top"><font size="2"><b>Top of
page</b></font></a></p>
<h2><a name="WEDNESDAY"><i>WEDNESDAY</i></a><i> SEPTEMBER 25</i> </h2>
<p><font size="4"><strong><i>17.00<br>
</i></strong></font><i>Lecture on History of Rhodes at the Rodini
Centre <br>
given by John Papachristodoulou, Director of the 22nd Ephorate of
Prehistoric and Classical Dodecanese Antiquities arranged by the
Greek Society of Writers</i></p>
<p><font size="4"><strong><i>22.00-24.00</i></strong></font><i><br>
Open Air poetry Reading in the Burg Church in the Old Town
(introductions by Yuri Pokalchuk, Ukraine and Sezer Duru, Turkey
and Irene Voyadzi-Haralambis from Rhodes)</i></p>
<p><font size="4"><strong><i>Special offer:</i></strong></font><i> </i><font
size="4"><strong><i>17.00-18.00</i></strong></font><i><br>
Swedish writers of children&#180;s books will read and tell
stories for Swedish children between five and ten years at Sun
Wing Amfi Theatre.<br>
Rhodes has a Swedish school with 110 children between five and
eighteen years of age. The writers will also visit the Swedish
school. The writers group consists of Max Lundgren, Bisse Falk,
Lasse Ekholm, Camilla Gripe, Ulla Keyling, Marianne
S&ouml;derb&auml;ck, Maj Samzelius, Gunila Ambj&ouml;rnsson,
Gunilla Lundgren, Susin Lindblom, Inger Brattstr&ouml;m,
Marie-Louise Wallin, Benkt Erik Hedin, Anita Nilsson and others.</i></p>
<p align="center"><a href="#MONDAY"><font size="2"><b>Monday 23</b></font></a><font
size="2"><b> | </b></font><a href="#TUESDAY"><font size="2"><b>Tuesday
24</b></font></a><font size="2"><b> | </b></font><a
href="#WEDNESDAY"><font size="2"><b>Wednesday 25</b></font></a><font
size="2"><b> | </b></font><a href="#THURSDAY"><font size="2"><b>Thursday
26</b></font></a><font size="2"><b> | </b></font><a
href="#FRIDAY"><font size="2"><b>Friday 27</b></font></a><font
size="2"><b> | </b></font><a href="#Top"><font size="2"><b>Top of
page</b></font></a></p>
<h2><a name="THURSDAY"><i>THURSDAY</i></a><i> SEPTEMBER 26</i> </h2>
<p><font size="4"><strong><i>17.00</i></strong></font><i><br>
</i><em>Official inauguration ceremony in the Acropolis Open Air
Theatre of Rhodes (Music, welcoming address by the Mayor of
Rhodes Giorgos Giannopoulous and speech by the Bulgarian poet
Blaga Dimitrova and Katerine Stenou, Director of section for
intercultural exchange UNESCO) </em></p>
<p><font size="4"><em><strong>19.00</strong></em></font><br>
<em>Reception offered by the Municipality of Rhodes in the
medieval castle KASTELO and addresses by delegates<br>
followed by performance &#147;Apocalypse Trial&#147;, an
inter-disciplinary mystery-play with puppets, using all
techniques, actors, stilt-walkers, music, song, mime, dance with
elements from literary classics. Production: Marionetteatern of
Stockholm, Michael Meschke. Actors and musicians from Sweden,
Greece, France, Argentina and Finland.</em> </p>
<p align="center"><a href="#MONDAY"><font size="2"><b>Monday 23</b></font></a><font
size="2"><b> | </b></font><a href="#TUESDAY"><font size="2"><b>Tuesday
24</b></font></a><font size="2"><b> | </b></font><a
href="#WEDNESDAY"><font size="2"><b>Wednesday 25</b></font></a><font
size="2"><b> | </b></font><a href="#THURSDAY"><font size="2"><b>Thursday
26</b></font></a><font size="2"><b> | </b></font><a
href="#FRIDAY"><font size="2"><b>Friday 27</b></font></a><font
size="2"><b> | </b></font><a href="#Top"><font size="2"><b>Top of
page</b></font></a></p>
<h2><a name="FRIDAY"><i>FRIDAY</i></a><i> SEPTEMBER 27</i> </h2>
<p><i>One-day cruise to Symi at self cost, approximately 3.000
GRD per person with Poetry reading on board</i>.<em> Return at 16
o'clock.</em></p>
<hr>
<p align="center"><font size="4"><em><strong>&quot;People in a
Landscape&quot;</strong></em></font><em> <br>
Throughout the week an art exhibition by artist Andreas Gedin <br>
illustrating what happens to a poem by Tomas Transtr&ouml;mer
while going through translations will be presented in the new
writers&#146; and translators&#146; centre on Laskou Street 10 A</em></p>
<hr>
<p align="center"><font size="4"><em><strong>For further
information:</strong></em></font><em><br>
</em><em><strong>Ewa A Kumlin<br>
</strong></em><em>Co-ordinator, Athens phone/fax: +30-1-681 01
56, e-mail: </em><a href="mailto:ewax@hol.gr"><em>ewax@hol.gr</em></a><em> <br>
</em><em><strong>Litsa Ftaklaki<br>
</strong></em><em>Rhodes City, phone: +30-241-232 61. fax:
+30-241-79 555 </em></p>
