<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<p align="center"><font size="7">Internet and Literature</font><br>
<font size="5">News from the seminar 23 september 1996</font></p>
<hr>
<p><img src="images/costas-lecture.JPG" align="right" hspace="10"
width="250" height="211">&#160;<strong>Costas Tsolakidis</strong>,
from the Aegean University of Rhodes invited intrested
participants of the seminar to &quot;hands-on&quot; training at
his computer studio at the Aegean University. Twelve participants
accepted his offer.Here the interested writers and translators
have the possibility to get familiar with Internet services as
Mail and World Wide Web (WWW). For his support some of the
speakers from the internet seminar on monday helped him with the
lecture.<br clear="all">
</p>
<p><img src="images/handson.JPG" align="left" hspace="10"
width="250" height="194">To the Left <strong>H&aring;kan Norelius</strong>
from Sweden gives instruction to one of the &quot;students&quot;.</p>
