<h2>Writers' Web</h2>

<p><b>Category: </b>About the Literary Scene<br>
<b>From: </b>Idar Lind (i-lind@online.no)<br>
<b>Date: </b>1997-01-21<br>
<b>Time: </b>15:28:24<br>
<b>Remote Name: </b>194.143.7.134<br>
</p>

<h3>Comments</h3>

<p>Norwegian authors' and playwrights' home on the Web are the
Norwegian Writers' Web. In English: <a
href="http://www.writers-web.no">http://www.writers-web.no</a>.
For those who understand Norwegian: The more comprehensive
service on <a href="http://www.litteraturnettet.no">http://www.litteraturnettet.no</a>.
</p>

<p> Our lists of Authors on the Web (<a
href="http://www.litteraturnettet.no/int-list.html)">http://www.litteraturnettet.no/int-list.html)</a>
and Authors with e-mail (<a
href="http://www.litteraturnettet.no/e-post.html)">http://www.litteraturnettet.no/e-post.html)</a>
includes writers from all around the world. </p>

<p> To be included you normally must have been published on paper
by a publishing house, or on stage / film / television. (Some
people find this a bit conservative, but that's the rules.) </p>

<p> Please help us develop this service! </p>

<p> Idar Lind i-lind@online.no</p>
</body>
