<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3O/DTD HTML//EN">

<html>
<head>
<title>Poetry Reading 23 september - Ileana Malancioiu</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
<meta name="FORMATTER" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<p><img src="images/ileana.jpg" align="right" hspace="10"
width="200" height="273"><font size="4">Three poems:<br>
</font><a href="#the tower of babel"><font size="4">the tower of
babel</font></a><font size="4"> | </font><a
href="#i cannot complain"><font size="4">i cannot complain</font></a><font
size="4"> | </font><a href="#prayer"><font size="4">prayer</font></a></p>
<h1><b>Ileana Malancioiu</b></h1>
<p>Born in January 23, 1940, in the village of Godeni, county of
Arges. Graduated from the Faculty of Philosophy, Bucharest
University, in 1968. Doctor's degree in Philosophy, with a thesis
on the tragic, 1975. </p>
<p><b>Published volumes:</b> </p>
<ul>
    <li>The Slaughtered Fowl (Pasarea taiata), Editura
        Tineretului, 1967 </li>
    <li>Unto Hieronymus (Catre Ieronim), Editura Albatros, 1970 </li>
    <li>The Queen's Heart (Inima reginei), Editura Eminescu, 1971 </li>
    <li>Poems (Poezii), Editura Cartea Romaneasca, 1973 </li>
    <li>Lilies for Her Ladyship the Bride (Crini pentru
        domnisoara mireasa), Editura Cartea Romaneasca, 1973, The
        Romanian Academy Prize 
        <ul>
            <li>Burnt Offering (Ardere de tot), Editura Cartea
                Romaneasca, 1976 </li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Tragic Guilt (Vina tragica) - The Greek Tragedians,
        Shakespeare Dostoyevsky, Kafka - an essay, Editura Cartea
        Romaneasca, 1976 </li>
    <li>Across the Forbidden Zone (Peste zona interzisa), Editura
        Cartea Romaneasca, 1979, Prize of The Writers' Union </li>
    <li>The Most Beautiful Poems (Cele mai frumoase poezii),
        Editura Albatros, 1980 </li>
    <li>My Sister Beyond (Sora mea de dincolo) Editura Cartea
        Romaneasca, 1980 </li>
    <li>The Line of Life (Linia vietii), Editura Cartea
        Romaneasca, Prize of The Writers' Union </li>
    <li>Peste zona interzisa / A travers la zone interdite,
        Editura Eminescu, 1984 </li>
    <li>The Climbing of the Mountain (Urcarea muntelui), Editura
        Albatros, 1985 </li>
</ul>
<p>Ileana Malancoiu has translated from German poetry. <br>
She publishes essays on Rumanian and word literature in the
press. </p>
<hr>
<p><b>Poems form Across the Forbidden Zone (Peste zona
interzisa), <br>
Editura Cartea Romaneasca, 1979</b> </p>
<h1><a name="the tower of babel">the tower of babel</a></h1>
<p>We had devised a new means of communicating <br>
In spite of the tongues that had got into a tangle <br>
And we had finished erecting the tower of Babel <br>
And it was tall and well placed and at the right angle </p>
<p>When I don't know how everything began to sway <br>
And he himself thought it was high time he came round <br>
To us up there and tangle the tongues once more <br>
But there was nothing left to tangle he found. </p>
<p>For we all spoke the same tongue <br>
I mean we would say the same thing each and all <br>
And he quietly watched us yell out the same word <br>
Which had absolutely no meaning at all. </p>
<hr>
<h1><a name="i cannot complain">i cannot complain</a></h1>
<p>I cannot complain of hunger <br>
All my food comes from heaven free <br>
But I'm afraid for the god <br>
That will have to feed on me. </p>
<p>I'm too dark and I'm too sad <br>
And my offering might seem <br>
Even leaner than it is <br>
Even bitterer to him. </p>
<p>In a lovely poppy field <br>
He could well my life blood pour <br>
While my flesh could well be kept <br>
To be shared among the poor. </p>
<hr>
<h1><a name="prayer">prayer</a></h1>
<p>Oedipus the king was led by the hand by his daughter Antigone <br>
King Lear by Cordelia, the one chased away <br>
From the kingdom for allegedly not loving him enough <br>
I could lead you, father, any day </p>
<p>As for me, I don't know if there will be anyone <br>
To accompany me in that hour most horrible <br>
When everything will be hidden to my eyes <br>
Us all I well know that it will be impossible. </p>
<p>O God, do not try to blind us all at once <br>
Take only every second man and delay the end <br>
Of the tragedy a little. Let everybody <br>
Have someone to lead him slowly by the hand. </p>
<hr>
<p><FORM NAME="buttonbar">
     <INPUT TYPE="button" VALUE="Back to Previous Page" onClick="history.back()">
</FORM>
</p>
</body>
