<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE> george jr. / february 1997 / features</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#336699" VLINK="#c0c0c0" ALINK="#c0c0c0">
<IMG SRC="/graphics/featuresb.gif" WIDTH=402 HEIGHT=34 ALIGN=left>
<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<HR>
<P>
<table cellpadding=10>
<tr><td>

<h2><A HREF="gambit.html">opening gambit</A></h2>
<!--text here-->
<IMG SRC="chess.gif" 	WIDTH=61 HEIGHT=47 ALIGN=left>

Welcome to February's free-for-all, a lark-about for readers with brains.  We call this literary monthly <b>george jr.</b> and, if I were you, I'd start with the <A HREF="gambit.html">introduction to the issue</A>, but it's your move. And don't you think it's time to put away the rub-on tattoos?



<P> 


<h2><A HREF="wideman.html">with john edgar wideman</a></h2>

<!--text here-->

   Rarely has the intimate relationship between author and reader
been explored more challengingly than it is in <b>The Cattle
Killing,</b> John Edgar Wideman's 13th book, and his first novel in
six years.<p>
  <P>


<h2><A HREF="olsen.html">lance olsen q &#38; a</a></h2>
<IMG SRC="icarus.gif" WIDTH=126 HEIGHT=124 ALIGN=right hspace=10 vspace=10>
<!--text here-->

<A HREF="http://www.uidaho.edu/~lolsen/">Lance Olsen</A>, Idaho
Writer-in-Residence and Philip K. Dick Award finalist for best science
fiction of 1995, is author of four novels, including <b>Tonguing the
Zeitgeist</b>, two short story collections, and six critical studies,
including the first book-length one about cyberpunk godfather <A
HREF="http://www.vkool.com/gibson/netindex.html">William Gibson</A>. 
Read on, landlubber.
<br clear=all>
<P>

<h2><A HREF="atwood.html">with margaret atwood</A></h2>

<!--text here-->
   Eleven years after she imagined a harsh authoritarian society
of the future in <B>The Handmaid's Tale</B>, the Canadian novelist
Margaret Atwood has turned her attention to an actual crime from
the past that poses more questions and riddles than it answers. Here she discusses her new novel, <B>Alias Grace</B>.<P>
<P>

<h2><A HREF="carson.html">on anne carson</a></h2>


<!--text here-->

Throughout  Anne Carson's <b>Plainwater</b>,  one hears the hyper-conscious, critical mind of an author with a powerfully clinical intelligence. You want to know what's the next big thing? It's Anne Carson.

<P>
</td>
<td valign=top>
<A HREF="index.html"><IMG SRC="home.gif" WIDTH=132 HEIGHT=36 border=0></A>
<br>
<br>
<a href="/feb97/arcadia.html"><IMG SRC="/graphics/gotoab.gif" WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=34 BORDER=0></a>
<br>
