<HEAD>
<TITLE> george jr. / february 1997 / departments</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#336699" VLINK="#c0c0c0" ALINK="#c0c0c0">
<IMG SRC="/graphics/deptsb.gif" WIDTH=402 HEIGHT=34 ALIGN=left>
<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<HR>
<P>
<table cellpadding=10>

<tr><td>

<h2><a href="kitty.html">ask kitty</a></h2>
<!--text here-->
February's advice from our unleashed cat's meow of a columnist. Don't even <b>think </b> about getting her fixed. Where would we be without her. (Well, <b>lost</b> leaps rapidly to mind.)
<P>

<h2><a href="npr/npr.html">national public rodeo</a>
<IMG SRC="horn.jpg" WIDTH=128 HEIGHT=65 hspace=10 vspace=10 ALIGN=left></h2>
<!--text here-->
We finally had a moment to reorganize our noteworthy links - and added about 30 more - at this month's newsstand for digerati. If you're a writer, you'll want to Bookmark the page; if you are a reader, Macolyte, IBMer, or a human being of adventurous sorts, you'll want to play their tunes. Until we realize our plans to build a <b>george jr.</b> theme park, this will have to do.

<P>
<h2><A HREF="austin.html">letter from austin</A></h2>
<IMG SRC="cowboy3.gif" WIDTH=120 HEIGHT=138 hspace=5 vspace=10 ALIGN=right>
Jeanne Claire van Ryzin reports on a city that never rides side-saddle. Listen, and don't be timid about trying those additional links, especially while listening to Orchestra Was' <b>Forever's a Long, Long Time</b>. If you decide Austin sounds too good to be true, move there and see for yourself. And take this <A HREF="austin.html">link</A> with you.

<P>
<h2><A HREF="keywest.html">letter from key west</A></h2>
<IMG SRC="snorkel.gif" WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=134 hspace=5 vspace=5 ALIGN=left>
<!--text here-->
Not content to merely present a basket overflowing with seasonal delights, Patrick A. Lennon continues his observations from our Southernmost city, where bombs burst in air and bums burst sometimes on the sidewalks. Check the temperature there, and feel crummy that you're somewhere else.

<br clear=all>

<P>
<h2><A HREF="spam.html">green eggs and spam</A></h2>

<!--text here-->
They roll in, in waves of green and each one of them accompanied by the sound of a million bee wings. Some are curious, others cool; all are uncooked. We're sticking a couple of headshakers in here each month. In none of them is the word "postmodern."

<h2><a href="back.html">back-issue generator</a></h2>
<!--text here-->
Literature is news that stays news," said that old cracker Ezra Pound. And we hope with this internet monthly, too. Take a look at the <a href="back.html">back-issue generator</a>, where most of this zine is archived and annotated.<br>

</td>

<td valign=top>

<A HREF="index.html"><IMG SRC="home.gif" WIDTH=133 HEIGHT=34 border=0></A>
