<html>
<head>
<title>george jr. / february 1997 / faq </title>
</head>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#336699" VLINK="#c0c0c0" ALINK="#c0c0c0">
<IMG SRC="/graphics/faqb.gif" WIDTH=402 HEIGHT=34 ALIGN=left>
<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<HR>
<P>
<table cellpadding=10>
<tr><td>
<blockquote>
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=5 color=red>What george jr. is</FONT><BR></CENTER>
<b>george jr.</b> is a monthly literary 'zine -- call it a boxcar, a kazoo, a 
magazine, whatever you like -- ever so devoted to literature, the 
national obsessions, fiction and news, sometimes, about the 
software and entertainment biz.
<p>

<b>george jr.</b> consists of views, frequently an artist's portfolio and 
news, much of it sent to our world headquarters via its faxline 
(614-899-9011), which usually <B>george jr.</B> remembers to leave turned on 
during the day before he heads to work.<BR>
<BR>

<HR WIDTH="75%"><BR>
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=5 color=red>Who george jr. is</FONT><BR></CENTER>
<b>george jr.</b> is written  and shaped by Powell, Ohio, resident <A HREF="http://wwww.coil.com/~gmyers">George Myers Jr.,</A> except where 
others' bylines appear and except for the p.r. stuff sent in by 
publicists. 
<b>george jr.</b> is books editor and  assistant arts editor for The Columbus 
<a href="http://www.dispatch.com">Dispatch</a> (614-461-5265, if you must call me at work 
and, if you do, and if I'm on deadline, kindly make it brief until <B>george jr.</B> can get back with you later). <P>
<A HREF="mailto:dnewman@equity.net">Daniel Newman</A> of my godfather site, <A HREF="http://www.columbuspages.com"> ColumbusPages</A>, does a whale of a job fixing my links and keeping my look the way it's intended to be. Anybody can have a magazine of her or his own. This is America, yes?<P>
<BR>
<HR WIDTH="75%"><BR>
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=5 color=red>What george jr. wants</FONT><BR>
</CENTER>
Editorial copy from you, for which we can pay neither a shilling nor a pence. <b>george jr.</b> is especially interested in Interesting Info smartly conveyed, and also original essays, short-short fiction and even reprints (which we secure permission to reprint, always, and for which we neither pay nor charge a dime). Especially coveted: columns on music and film.<P>
And he wants to keep his birth name.

<p>

<b>george jr. </b> finally has a scanner, so kindly send your art or prints, but not slides, which require more technology than I have. Send letters as <A HREF="mailto:jr@georgejr.com">email</A> or disks, via snail mail, to <B>george jr.</B>, Box 2962, Columbus, Ohio 43216-2962 (US of A).

<p>

<CENTER><B>Now, on with the show.</B></CENTER>
<BR>
<HR WIDTH="75%">

<SUB>
<B>george jr.</B> is especially interested in the nation's book culture, whose residue is amply represented on the web. For starters, you might want to see this month's National Public Rodeo, within this issue of<B> george jr.</B> The page includes a load of literary links.  If commerce is your thing, start here:<BR>

