<blockquote>

<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=4 CELLPADDING=4>

<TR VALIGN=Top>
<td>
<img src="/graphics/gambit.gif" hspace=10 width=150 height=100 ALIGN=left ALT="">
Welcome to the February issue of <b>george jr.</b>, the internet monthly 
that takes only "Well, uh, OK, yes" for an answer.<P>



So, what's your question?<P>


Well, what's in this issue? News of another fieldtrip to Lilac Valley, 
N.Y.? Or what my  grandfather might more than once said?<P>



Well, this is not a technological slag heap, I assure you. Nothing that 
buzzes or pings. Nothing about chat groups. No music here, Bubba. Nothing 
about  <A HREF="http://www.backweb.com">Backweb</A>, <A 
HREF="http://www.xing.com">Xing</A>,
 <A HREF="http://www.vdo">VDO</A>,
<A HREF="http://www.vxtreme.com">Vxtreme</A>,
 <A HREF="http://www.pointcast.com">Pointcast knockoffs</A>,
<A HREF="http://www.vocaltec.com">VocalTec conferencing</A>,
 <A HREF="http://www.net2phone.com">Net2Phone Direct</A>,
<A HREF="http://www.symantec.com">Symantic Faxing</A>,
<A HREF="http://www.microsoft.com">NetMeeting 2.0</A> or
<A HREF="http://www.goliath.wpine.com/cu-seeme.html"> CUSeeMe</A>.
<br clear=all>
<BR>
  

Well, why not?<P>

Because, my little cookie-head, <B>george jr</B>. is about words and 
people. You want to chat ? Use the telephone. You want to see an animated 
face? Knock on your neighbor's door at 3 a.m.  Wanna hear some tunes? 
Turn on your CD player, ferheavensakes.<P>

<!--IMG SRC="weber.jpg" WIDTH=137 HEIGHT=220 hspace=10 vspace=10 align=right-->

No, it's content that is king at <B>george jr.</B>, which this month 
includes features on the novelists <B>Margaret Atwood, John Edgar 
Wideman, Lance Olsen</B> and a clarion call from<B> Raymond Federman</B>. 
Oh sure, we'll play with you a bit - in <B>monkey buttons</B>, for 
example, because the humanoid was born to tinker and to try and raise a 
grin - but all the while we'll tilt you back to words, news, literature 
and info. <B>Ask Kitty</B> advises, gently, on how you might revise your 
life. <P>
 As always, there is more: <B>Patrick A. Lennon</B> offers the news from 
Key West.<B> Jeanne Claire van Ryzin </b>reports, blithely, on the  
Austin Lyric Opera, now entering its 10th season.  <b>Richard Grayson 
Esq.</B> is all tied up, at the moment, in panty hose.
And more and more, courtesy of <B>David Baker, Nicholas A. Basbanes, </b> 
that old drayhorse <A HREF="http://www.coil.com/~gmyers">george jr.</A>. 
and a <I>trio con brio</I> with green megs of spam.<P>
Next month: The battle for PEN; all-mighty paradigms; a report from 
Habitat for Humanity  in Africa; interviews with three incredible writers 
worth your time; a pinch of pepper; a jot of zany; updates from live 
wires everywhere.
Meantime, ploughshares and popcorn to all. <P>
You count, big time. Do read on. And feel free to leave <A 
HREF="mailto:jr@georgejr.com">your voice print</A>.<P>
<P>

