<head>

<title>george jr. / february 1997 / arcadia / poem by david baker</title>

</head>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#336699" VLINK="#c0c0c0" ALINK="#c0c0c0">	

<a href="arcadia.html"><IMG SRC="/graphics/gotoab.gif" WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=34 BORDER=0 align=left></a>

<A HREF="index.html"><IMG SRC="home.gif" WIDTH=133 HEIGHT=34 border=0 align=right></A>

<br clear=all>

<hr>

<br>



<H3>poem by david baker</H3> 

<blockquote>

<BR>

      <b><h4> council meeting</h4></b><br>
<p>
        The latest uproar:  to allow Wendy's <Br>
        to build another fast food burger shack <br>
        on four acres of wetlands near Raccoon Creek<br>
        or to permit the conservationist<br>
<p>
        well-to-do citizenry to keep their green<br>
        space and thus assure long, unsullied views<br>
        from their redwood decks, picture windows,<br>
        and backyards chemically rich as golf greens.<br>
<p>
        The paper's rife with spats, accusations,<br>
        pieties both ways.  Wendy's promises<br>
        flowers, jobs.  The citizens want this, too,<br>
        but want it five miles away where people<br>
<p>
        don't care about egrets, willows, good views.<br>
        Oh, it's going to be a long night:  call <br>
        out for pizza, somebody brew some tea.<br>
        Then we'll all stand up for what we believe.<br>


<br>
<!-- Horizontal Line Tag --><HR>
<blockquote>
<A HREF="mailto:baker@CC.DENISON.EDU"><b>David Baker</b></A>
teaches literature and creative writing at Denison University. He is the author of the poetry collections <i>After the Reunion; Sweet Home, Saturday Night; Haunts;</i> and <i>Laws of the Land</i>; as well as this year's<i> Meter in English: A Critical Engagement.</i>
</blockquote>
</blockquote>



<HR><BR>

<a href="arcadia.html"><IMG SRC="/graphics/gotoab.gif" WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=34 BORDER=0 align=left></a>

<A HREF="index.html"><IMG SRC="home.gif" WIDTH=133 HEIGHT=34 border=0 align=right></A>    
</BODY>

</HTML>

