<menu>
Ralph Nader.  Why?   1--because he has a proven and lengthy track record of representing The  People (having taken on and beaten a multi national [GM]; and 2--because abortion is personal  and not a political issue.  Some additional reasons:  he wouldn't have to please big money or  play ball with Congress either.</menu><BR>
<P><HR WIDTH=50%><P>

