How about Doctor Jack Kevorkian.<BR>
Much of the Federal Government could use a good mercy killing.</menu>
<P><HR WIDTH=50%><P>


<B>From: 72760.2013@compuserve.com</B><P>
<menu>
Of the current contenders, the answer is easy: Bill Clinton. I believe he has
done an admirable job under difficult circumstances.  He may not have managed
all his initiatives well, but his heart has always been in the right place.  I
don't believe the Republicans as a group--and Dole who is apparently a
shoe-in--has sufficient compassion for the poor.
<P>
 That said, I don't believe anyone has the moxie to do what's necessary to solve
this country's major problems.  I want a candidate willing to put a $1 gallon
tax on gasoline (introduced perhaps 20c ata time every six months).  That does a
lot of things.
<P>
<menu><nl>
<li>It will raise staggering amounts of cash that will balance the budget \not on
th ebacks of th epoor but on the backs of those who drive (and pollute) the
most.
<li>It will probably help our balance of payments problem, since presumably
people will drive less and reduce the demand for gasoline reducing the amount we
import.
<li>It will probably force people out of the trucks they've been buying (including Jeeps and Explorers and Caravans) into more economical vehicals and into mass transit.  This improves npot only our financial problems, but environmental ones as well.
<li>It will force american auto manufacturers to concentrate on developing and
marketing smaller cars.
<li>While there will certainly be some inflationary aspect to this, that will
presumably offset by animproved american economy (because of balanced budget)
creating more jobs, gasoline prices going down because of reduced consumption
and the gradual introduction of the tax.
</nl></menu>
I've probably told you more than you want to know.  And I haven't even discussed
my environmental or crime fighting packages.  Sadly I was not born in this
country, so I cannot become President. </menu>
<P><HR WIDTH=50%><P>

<B>From: mricksec@freenet.columbus.oh.us</B><P>
<menu>
me i'd like to see cher.  why should sonny be the only one with political
aspirations?  besides, it is in keeping with the tradition of so many,
shall we say, third world countries, in which the wife or daughter of a
deposed male rises to political heights.  or what about chastity?  no,
cher has the better hair.</menu>
