<title>george jr. / july 1996 / politics / coffee break, 2nd cup</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" LINK="#2F4F2F" VLINK="#c0c0c0" ALINK="#c0c0c0">
<a href="../july/politics.html"><IMG SRC="../graphics/gotop.gif" WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=34 BORDER=0 align=left></a>
<A HREF="index.html"><IMG SRC="../graphics/home.gif" WIDTH=133 HEIGHT=34 border=0 align=right></A>
<br clear=all>
<hr>
<br>
<H2>coffee break, 2nd cup</H2>
<P>
It's mid-summer. What a better way to prepare for the dog days of August than by whipping up Dirt Pudding - a light summery dessert to put a smile on your face (and add  infinitesmal additions to the love handles at your sides. ) This totally non-caloric dessert (not) is great with a chocolate cappucino, but any flavor cappucino will do.
<P>
Dirt pudding:
<MENU>
<UL>
<LI>1 large package of Oreo cookies
<LI>1 8oz. package of cream cheese
<LI>1/2 stick butter
<LI>3 cups of mik
<LI>1 teaspoon vanilla
<LI>2 packages instant vanilla pudding
<LI>1-16oz. cartoon of Cool Whip
<LI>1 cup powdered sugar
</UL>
</MENU>
<P>
Blend milk and packages of instant vanilla pudding. Refrigerate for 10-15 minutes. Blend together cream cheese, butter, and powdered suger. Mix vanilla and pudding mixture. Fold in Cool Whip.
<P>
In a large bowl place 1/2 of the mixture. Top with 1/2 bag of crushed Oreos. Cover with remainder of mixture. Top with the remainder of cookies.
<P>
If you are trying to watch your weight, you can subsitute each of items with its reduced fat version. For example, Oreos now come in reduced fat, as does the cream cheese, butter,  and Cool Whip. Go further and use skim or 1 percent milk instead of whole milk and you'll really have a a dessert that you don't have to feel guilty about. The nice part is though you can barely tell the difference between the low-fat and regular recipe.
<P>
Enjoy.

<P>
