<title>george jr. / july 1996 / departments / the joy of lex / answers</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" LINK="#2F4F2F" VLINK="#c0c0c0" ALINK="#c0c0c0">
<a href="../july/departments.html"><IMG SRC="../graphics/gotod.gif" WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=34 BORDER=0 align=left></a>
<A HREF="index.html"><IMG SRC="../graphics/home.gif" WIDTH=133 HEIGHT=34 border=0 align=right></A>
<br clear=all>
<hr>
<br>

<H2>the joy of lex</H2>
<P>
OK, Americentrics: Sorry about the shouting. Here are the answers
<P>
The words and their origins:
<menu><menu>
  thug - Hindustani<BR>
  loafed - Danish<BR>
  damask - Hebrew<BR>
  table - Latin<BR>
  cafe - French<BR>
  balcony - Italian<BR>
  Wednesday - Anglo-Saxon<BR>
  goulash - Hungarian<BR>
  chocolate - Nahuatl<BR>
  caste - Portuguese<BR>
  kimono - Japanese<BR>
  lemon - Arabic<BR>
  frock - Old High German<BR>
  crimson - Sanskrit<BR>
  angora - Turkish<BR>
  shawl - Persian<BR>
  canny - Scottish<BR>
  smuggler - Dutch<BR>
  tea - Chinese<BR>
  cargoes - Spanish<BR>
  paper - Greek <BR>
</menu></menu>
<P>
Thanks, Robert Hendrickson, for your book <i>The Literary Life and Other Curiosities,</i> which educates us so.
<P>
