<table cellpadding=10>
<tr><td>
<h2><A HREF="gambit.html">opening gambit</A></h2>
<IMG SRC="chess.jpg" hspace=10 WIDTH=128 HEIGHT=88 ALIGN=left>



<!--text here-->

Welcome to 1997 and January's free-for-all internet monthly. Just between you and me, we call it <b>george jr.</b> If I were you, I'd start here, but it's your move.

<br clear=all>

<P> 
<IMG ALIGN=right SRC="mouth.jpg" hspace=10 WIDTH=128 HEIGHT=102 border=0>
<h2><A HREF="neil.html">neil steinberg q &#38; a</a></h2>

<!--text here-->
My goodness, have you ever met an essayist who was so ticked off by so many things? Boy is he ever annoyed - and <i>The Alphabet of Modern Annoyances</i> tells why.

<br clear=all>
<P>


<h2><A HREF="sharp.html">paula sharp q&#38; a</a></h2>

<IMG ALIGN=left SRC="crow.jpg" hspace=10 WIDTH=128 HEIGHT=118 border=0>
<!--text here-->
  The novelist, most recently of<I> Crows Over a Wheatfield,</I> tells why her profession as an attorney so often lets down when it comes to protecting the rights of abused women and their children.
<br clear=all>
<P>




<h2><A HREF="napora.html">praisesong: meridel le sueur</A></h2>

<!--text here-->
<I>Bullhead</I> editor, poet and critic Joe Napora pays tribute to one of the late, great ones.

<P>

<h2><A HREF="webb.html">the literary fruitcake</a></h2>


<!--text here-->
In this work of fiction, short-story writer Don Webb contributes a tale of many cities and times - all baked into <I>A Spell for the Fulfillment of Desire.</I>

<P>






</td>



<td valign=top>



<A HREF="index.html"><IMG SRC="/graphics/home2.gif" WIDTH=132 HEIGHT=36 border=0></A>



<br>



