<table cellpadding=10>

<tr><td>



<h2><A HREF="gambit.html">opening gambit</A></h2>

<!--text here-->
Welcome to the September issue. Stop here first to see - and this is no place for monocles  - what awaits you.

<P> 

<h2><A HREF="qawarlick.html">q &#38; a</a></h2>

<!--text here-->
Young turk Ashley Warlick is the youngest novelist ever to have won the Houghton Mifflin Literary Fellowship. The sky's the limit.

<P>
<h2><A HREF="qapower.html">q &#38; a</a></h2>
<!--text here-->
Novelist Susan Power has a book due in 1997. Here she talks about her gift of storytelling.

<P>
<h2><A HREF="qafurst.html">q &#38; a</A></h2>

<!--text here-->
Spy guy Alan Furst talks about espionage and susceptible patriotism. Remember Wang Pi's words: "It's the will that creates disorder. When the mind is empty, the will is weak."

<P>

<h2><A HREF="olsen.html">fiction</A></h2>

<!--text here-->

Idaho writer Lance Olsen offers up a wee something about disorder in Seattle.

<P>
<h2><A HREF="offal.html">something offal</A></h2>

<!--text here-->

Award-winning Canadian essayist Margaret Visser, who has graced these digitzied pages before, offers a word or two about, well, something offal.

<P>

<h2><A HREF="trekkies.html">a trifle for trekkies</A></h2>

<!--text here-->
News for trekheads about a TV special, a way of life - nay, dear reader - the way of a television show's afterlife.

<P>


</td>

<td valign=top>

<A HREF="index.html"><IMG SRC="/graphics/home.gif" WIDTH=133 HEIGHT=34 border=0></A>

