<table cellpadding=10>
<tr><td>
<h2><A HREF="gambit.html">opening gambit</A></h2>

<!--text here-->
Generally shy about exclamation marks, let us nevertheless say: Welcome to the October issue! Start here for the inside story.

<P> 

<h2><A HREF="anshaw.html">carol anshaw q &#38; a</a></h2>

<!--text here-->
You wake up and - yikes! - your partner isn't there anymore. The novelist of <I>Aquamarine</I> is back with a thriller.

<P>
<h2><A HREF="yglesias.html">rafael yglesias q &#38; a</a></h2>
<!--text here-->
This guy has a cure for evil, and it's his latest novel. Take two in the morning and you'll feel better all day.

<P>
<h2><A HREF="artnot.html">fiction: art does (not!) exist</A></h2>

<!--text here-->
Performance artist/novelist Rose Drexler has something or two or three or four to say about life, art, arts agencies and relationships in her rant-as-novel novel, which we're happy to excerpt for you.

<P>

<h2><A HREF="tomatoes.html">fiction: lost tomatoes</A></h2>

<!--text here-->

<b>george jr.</b> is always misplacing his fruits and vegetables. Thank heavens that Greek novelist Vassilis Vassilikos happened by with a bushel of fictive goodies. Here, have one on us.

<P>
<H2>faq</H2>
<a href="what.html">What george jr. is</a>
<br>
<a href="who.html">Who george jr. is</a>
<br>
<a href="wants.html">What george jr. wants</a>

<P>


</td>

