<table cellpadding=10>
<tr><td>
<P>
<h2><A HREF="uneasy.html">uneasy chair</A></h2>
<!--text here-->
If you sit on it, it will make a funny sound. But it's more comfortable than the ground. Seriously, this has nothing whatsoever to do with Edward Asner,  Steven Bochco, Charles Kuralt, Angela Lansbury (we tried to block her), Aaron Spelling, Lew R. Wasserman  and the producing team of Marcy Carsey and Tom Werner having just been inducted the Academy of  Television Arts & Sciences' Television Academy Hall of Fame.

<H2><A HREF="beatific.html">beatific advice</A></H2>

<!--text here-->
Stanley Crawford, what a guy. He has some advice that will leave you giddy, if not J. Paul Getty.

<P>
<H2><A HREF="gallery.html"-->gallery</A></H2>

<!--text here-->
Images from the hands and mind of artist <!-- MailTo Tag --><A HREF="MAILTO:rnewma@ibm.net">Linda Leviton</A>.

<p>


<H2><A HREF="wh4.html">white house e-mail: raw & unplugged</A></H2>

<!--text here-->
Live from the White House, it's Oliver North, Colin Powell and the National Security folks' trove of no-longer-secret email about the Iran-Contra brouhaha.
<ul><font size=2><b>Archive:</b><br>
<li><a href="wh1.html">Week 1</a>
<li><a href="wh2.html">Week 2</a>
<li><a href="wh3.html">Week 3</a>
<!--li><a href="wh4.html">Week 4</a-->
</ul></font>
<P>
<H2><A HREF="ruined.html">ruined by reading</A></H2>
<!--text here-->
Our literate listener Nicholas A. Basbanes takes us into the mind and book of Lynne Sharon Schwartz, who has read too much for her own darn good.

<P>
<H2><A HREF="home.html">Beth Powning's 'Home'</a></H2>

<!--text here-->
O, Canada! How sweet the landscape can be.

<P>
</td>

<td valign=top>

<A HREF="index.html"><IMG SRC="/graphics/home.gif" WIDTH=133 HEIGHT=34 border=0></A>

