<h2><A HREF="gambit.html">opening gambit</A></h2>



<!--text here-->

The welcome to December's loaf-about, free-for-all internet monthly. Just between you and me, we call <b>george jr.</b>



<P> 



<h2><A HREF="wendellberry.html">wendell berry q &#38; a</a></h2>



<!--text here-->

Technology is swell, but good neighborliness is better, says the award-winning novelist, essayist, poet and occasional ranter.



<P>

<h2><A HREF="haroldbloom.html">harold bloom's latest obsession</a></h2>

<!--text here-->
  "The problem with this book is that it's impossible to classify as a genre. It's not really a book about religion, even though the last chapter is a sermon. Maybe, in some sense, this entire book is a gnostic sermon. That's probably the answer - a gnostic sermon."

<P>




<h2><A HREF="margaretvisser.html">facing margaret visser</A></h2>

<!--text here-->
Canadian essayist Margaret Visser this month examines the most unapprehendable of things: the human face.


<P>

<h2><A HREF="keywest.html">letter from key west</a></h2>


<!--text here-->
Patrick A. Lennon's short story, 'Fat Albert,' launches his ongoing 'letter' from the Southernmost town in the USA.

<P>






</td>



