<H2>we the peephole</H2>Ladieeeees and gentlemeeeen!
<P>
Step right up to the Circus Maximus of Celebrity America!
<P>
If we haven't seen you in<i> people magazine</i> or <i>Us,</i> well, youjust aren't one of the Gods of our commodity culture.    Our readers/writers are bottom feeders who have always something to chant, rant and rave about; and they have eyes that have seen. Here's what we're talking about in August:  the celebs we've seen here, there and in your moma's kitchen.
 <P>
<hr>
<p>
<pre>
from: glp1@psu.edu
The decades-long rumors that Hal Linden Jr. and Omar Shariff 
are the same person have finally been put to rest.  The two of them 
(no, there were not any mirrors or David Copperfield to be seen) 
were observed lunching at a local eatry. Linden keeping trim with 
a light salad and Omar with his customary rack of lamb. Thank 
goodness this rumor is dead.  I could never bring myself 
to call Dr.  Zhivago "Barney."

from: twlamb@best.com
Mario Cuomo. He is a decent human being, intelligent and straight  
foreward. New York will regret his loss as governor.

from: deall@ten-nash.ten.k12.tn.us
 I saw Elvis walking out of the local Food Lion.   Last week, 
I spotted Garth Brooks in Nashville slurping a slurpy.

 from: dwm7@psuvm.psu.edu
 I urinated in the Chicago Airport men's room between two 
Monkees (1968),  Micky and Peter.

 from: mikek@travsoft.com
 Once my wife sat two tables away from Bob Barker at a restaurant.  
(I don't  think he was eating a poodle.)  
 And there also was the time while in the gallery of the Doral Open, 
my mom was hit in the foot by Sam Snead's golf ball.  His lie was 
definitely not  improved.

 from: bwiseman@mail.wsu.edu
Earlier this day I had occation to view F. Lee Bailey making nice 
with former rival   Clark at a west L.A. ristorante, frequented by 
only the rich and oh so fashionable.  Seems as late that he may be 
in need of some legal advice.

 from: sgtesq@execpc.com
 Elvis was sighted at the Whitehouse last night;  however, upon closer
 inspection it turned out to be President Clinton, who had not washed
 his hair in  several  days.  

from: jamienelson@fairisaac.com
 A "friend of the Dead" reports seeing  Jerry Garcia dressed as an Elvis  
impersonator in a Marin County, CA, supermarket produce section. 

from: jneer@equity.net
While enjoying a round of golf, I spotted George Voinovich and Bob 
Dole arguing over a golf ruling.  Apparently, George thought Bob's 
ball was  out of bounds because it went way too far to the right...

from: sam.erde@abacus.nlbbs.com
I had lunch with David Erde last week! He treated.  Even Bill Clinton 
himself can't make this claim!

 from: spits@primenet.com
 I was waiting for a flight at Kansas City International, which was 
delayed. I had my cocker with me and Billy Joel walked over and 
played with my dog and talked for  20 minutes. I'm glad my dog 
didn't bite Billy.

from: slawinski@enteractive.com
Bill Clinton, Boris Yeltsin, and Bill Gates were called in by God. 
God informed them that he was very unhappy about what was going 
on in this  world. Since things were so bad, he told the three that he 
was destroying  the Earth in 3 days.  They were all allowed to return 
to  their homes and  businesses, and tell their friends and colleagues 
what was happening.

God did tell them though, that no matter what they did he was 
"not"  changing his mind.  So, . . . . .  Bill Clinton went in and 
told his staff, "I have good news and bad news for you. First the 
good news . . . there "is" a God.  The bad news is  that he is destroying 
the Earth in 3 days."

Boris Yeltsin went back and told his staff, "I have bad news and 
more bad news. The first was . . . there "is" a God.  The second 
is that he is  destroying the Earth in 3 days."

Bill Gates went back and told his staff, "I have good news and 
good news. First . . . God thinks I am one of the three most 
important people in  the world.  Second . . . you don't have to fix 
the bugs in Win95."

