<head>
<title>george jr. / august 1996 / departments / weights & measures</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" LINK="#2F4F2F" VLINK="#c0c0c0" ALINK="#c0c0c0">
<a href="../august/departments.html"><IMG SRC="../graphics/gotod.gif" WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=34 BORDER=0 align=left></a>
<A HREF="index.html"><IMG SRC="../graphics/home.gif" WIDTH=133 HEIGHT=34 border=0 align=right></A>
<br clear=all>
<hr>
<br>
<H2>weights & measures</H2>
What is beauty? That's the word we're measuring this month. Jan Leibovitz Alloy measured its inseams and cuffs, and has come up with a better than workable 18-part definition.
<P>
Hers, that is, of beauty:
<blockquote>
(1)  <i>As You Like It,</i> Bartolli, Clapton, the Beatles,  <i>Casablanca, Starry Night, </i>the  <i>Brandenburgs,</i> the Glass family, Fred Astaire (with or without), Streisand, swing ... the usual suspects
<P>
(2) purple
<P>
(3) a welcome and graceful death
<P>
(4) snow diamonds glimmering silently slowly from the shovel
<P>
(5) oreagnancy, childbirth and, yes, even labor
<P>
(6) Gershwin, of course - and Fielding
<P>
(7)  <i>The Philadelphia Story</i> except for that <i>hat</i>
<P>
(8) eye wrinkles
<P>
(9) three stars, meditation, Havdalah
<P>
(10) the aqua/velvet guilelessness of a prepubescent chest
<P>
(11) cycle flight
<P>
(12) clamorous intersections of flatware, tabletops, pop bottles, flooring, and Mommy's best pots and pans
<P>
(13) football season: the russet thrill of burning leaves
<P>
(14) pesto and brownies (mine)
<P>
(15) Avraham Dov and his namesakes
<P>
(16) candlelight, Ferris wheels, Ginger's dresses, and swings
<P>
(17) birthdays on the down side of the bell curve
<P>
(18)  all as I perceive it 
</blockquote>
<P>
