<H2>Who george jr. is</H2>
<blockquote>
<p align=left><br>

<b>george jr.</b> is George Myers Jr., books editor for The Columbus 
<a href="http://www.dispatch.com">Dispatch</a> (614-461-5265, if you must call me at work 
and, if you do, and if I'm on deadline, could you kindly make it quite 
brief).
<p>
   If you want to be bored, you can learn about <a href="http://www.coil.com/~gmyers">me</a>, 
although <b>george jr.</b> is really what it's all about.
   <p>
The content of <b>george jr.</b> is written by George Myers Jr., except where 
others' bylines appear and except for the p.r. stuff sent in by 
publicists for the various firms identified in  <a href="sources.html">Sources</a>, 
or other outfits that haven't yet appeared as Sources but who, shucks, 
nevertheless are.
<p>
   Anybody can have a magazine of her or his own. This is America, yes?

