<br><br>
<H3>Austen Heart of It All in October</H3>
 Filmmakers Wes Craven (NIGHTMARE ON ELM STREET) and Emilio Estevez (THE WAR AT HOME) have  been added to the already impressive list attending the 3rd annual Austin Heart of Film Festival it was announced today by festival  directors Barbara Morgan and Marsha Milam.  Dedicated to the screenwriter and the script, the festival, held in Austin, Texas October 10-13, is fast becoming the place to be this fall for screenwriters, producers  and filmmakers.
   <p>  Screenwriters scheduled to make the trip to Austin  include:  Oscar winner Chris McQuarrie (THE USUAL SUSPECTS), Eric Roth (FORREST  GUMP), Randall Wallace (BRAVEHEART), Patrick Duncan (MR. HOLLAND'S OPUS), Bill Broyles & Al Reinert (APOLLO 13), Chris Wilkerson & Steve Rivele (NIXON), John Lee Hancock (MIDNIGHT IN THE GARDEN OF GOOD AND EVIL), Bill Wittliff (LEGENDS OF THE FALL) and James Duff (THE WAR AT  HOME).
   <p>  Columbia Pictures President of Production Barry Josephson will  be joined by HBO producer Stu Smiley and producers Polly Platt  (BOTTLE ROCKETS, BIG) and Karen Murphy (DRUGSTORE COWBOY, THIS IS SPINAL TAP)  at this year's conference.
    <p> The Festival consists of a screenwriters' conference by day and  a film festival by night. The Festival also sponsors a  script  competition which received a record 2,200 screenplays this year.
    <p> Columbia Pictures optioned EXCESS BAGGAGE, penned by 1994 Competition winning screenwriter Max Adams. The film is  currently  in production starring Alicia Silverstone, Benicio Del Toro and  Christopher Walken.  Semi-finalist Ron Peer's screenplay, GOOD-BYE LOVER, was optioned by Gotham Entertainment from the 1995 Competition and  Roland Joffe, Oscar-winning director of THE KILLING FIELDS, is set to  direct. Production is scheduled to begin during the summer of 1996.


<P><hr width=75%><P>


<h3>Hulk Makes Smashing TV Return</h3>
  Marvel's  Hulk storms  onto UPN this fall sure to thrill legions of viewers while making competitors  green with envy. Stand back. <b>george jr.</b> had no chance to get the part.
   <p>  The new animated series willanchor UPN Kids Sunday morning line-up. Viewers will be quick to latch on to The Incredible Hulk as his story jumps directly from the pages of the perennial best-selling Marvel comic  book. People familiar with the 70's television hit and the comic know Hulk's story began when the awesome, uncontrollable might of a gamma radiation experiment
<p>Bruce Banner into the massive green being. Now, the  misunderstood  man-monster roams the planet, with Banner searching for a cure to tame monster  dwelling within him. Who can't relate?

<P><hr width=75%><P>

<h3>GAF Sells WAXQ</h3>

 GAF Corporation announced completed the sale of its New York City radio station, WAXQ-FM,
to Entertainment Communications, Inc. (Entercom) for $90 million. Entercom simultaneously swapped WAXQ-FM to Viacom Inc. for three of Viacom's radio stations serving Seattle, KBSG-AM, KBSG-FM, and KNDD-FM. 
 <p>  GAF Corporation, a Fortune 1000 Company, is a leading manufacturer
of specialty chemicals and building materials through its two principal subsidiaries, International Specialty Products Inc. and Building Materials Corporation of America.
   

<P><hr width=75%><P>

 <h3>Dogg Pound To Hit Center Stage</h3>

  

 Food has finally arrived for the dogg pound! Premiere rap artists 2Pac, Snoop Doggy Dogg and Tha Dogg Pound will feed their hungry crew of fans when they perform together on their "All Eyez on US" 25 city U.S. tour starting early October, 1996.  Cities, arenas, ticket prices, and sale dates will be announced in the near future.
    <p> Presented by Daedalus Entertainment Finance Company, L.L.C. (Def Com), a renowned concert promotion company headquartered in St. Louis, Chairman and C.E.O., Stephen M. Coleman and a crew of prominent industry professionals, are responsible for bringing the masters of rap to key cities across the country. "2Pac, Snoop and Tha Dogg Pound felt that we could handle three of the
"phattest" and largest rappers on stage in 20,000 seat arenas.  They knew we would handle the tour with the utmost respect and professionalism."
    <p> First in the series of wide-scale high profile concert tours, Coleman promises that this tour will run as smooth as ice. Uh, yeah.

<P><hr width=75%><P>

<h3>Relativity Is No. 1 Indie Label</h3>

 Relativity Records led the other indies as the country's #1 independent label according to SoundScan's half-year results. This is especially impressive  considering  that Relativity announced its status as strictly an urban music label just six months ago.
  <p>    Relativity has enjoyed burgeoning success with its eclectic  roster of hip hop talent as well as its high-profile associated label  signings for which Relativity markets, promotes and distributes through its  indie distributor, RED. During the past four years, Relativity has  grown  into a major player in the urban marketplace developing such artists  as Common, Dru Down, Fat Joe, Mac Mall, and The Beatnuts.  Relativity  has also attracted such key label signings as Eazy-E's Ruthless Records (quadruple platinum-selling Bone Thugs-N-Harmony, MC Ren) and  Tony
Draper's Suave Records (gold-selling Eightball & MJG, South Circle).
     

