<title>george jr. / september 1996 / departments / the joy of lex</title>
</head>

<body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" LINK="#2F4F2F" VLINK="#c0c0c0" ALINK="#c0c0c0">

<a href="/september/departments.html"><IMG SRC="/graphics/gotod.gif" WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=34 BORDER=0 align=left></a>

<A HREF="index.html"><IMG SRC="/graphics/home.gif" WIDTH=133 HEIGHT=34 border=0 align=right></A>

<br clear=all>

<hr>

<br>


<H2>the joy of lex</H2> 
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<b> george jr.</b> likes words - long ones, short ones, think ones, skinny ones, lean ones, means ones. But never puns. And vowels and abbreviations are swell, too. Often.   This month's lex  is a list - holy gadzooks, a mere list! - of vanity license plates spotted and logged by Steve and Patricia Wynn Brown of Columbus, Ohio.

Here goes:
<UL><LI> MRPNUT
<LI> MSCUE
<LI> RU4OSU
<LI> EGOTRP
<LI> MIS LED
<LI> STK MKT
<LI> UZ2BRCH
<LI> K PASA
<LI> JOY TOY
<LI> IM 4U QT
<LI> I SWEAT
<LI> 4 MY DOG
<LI> FLAW LES
<LI> W WONKA
<LI> UP 2 YU
<LI> BEAM ME
<LI> KIK BUT
<LI> LIVN EZ
<LI> I WED 4U
<LI> 1 LOUD Z
<LI> 1 LIMEY
<LI> LST LAF
<LI> MR HAIR
<LI> FLIN BY
<LI> T TIME 9
<LI> GO N4 IT
<LI> AUDITU
<LI> ARF ARF
<LI> QUE PASA
<LI> U R FOXY
<LI> GRRR
<LI> IAMTAN
<LI> GOP4ME
<LI> LUNATK
<LI> MY PERK
<LI> ANEWME
<LI> 2 STEPR
<LI> BALD
<LI> CRE8IV
<LI> 2IFBYC
<LI> LUV ZIT
<LI> NYT OWL
<LI> IN2XTC
</UL>
  

CRE8IV? Well, we'll have to take the car's word for it. If you spot any <i>genuinely </i>cool roadside attractions, send 'em along to <a href=mailto:gmyers@coil.com>george jr.</a>
</BLOCKQUOTE>

</BODY>

