<head>

<title>george jr. / september 1996 / departments / weights & measures</title>

</head>

<body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" LINK="#2F4F2F" VLINK="#c0c0c0" ALINK="#c0c0c0">

<a href="/september/departments.html"><IMG SRC="/graphics/gotod.gif" WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=34 BORDER=0 align=left></a>

<A HREF="index.html"><IMG SRC="/graphics/home.gif" WIDTH=133 HEIGHT=34 border=0 align=right></A>

<br clear=all>

<hr>

<br>

<H2>weights & measures</H2>

Voyager's award-winning and controversial history CD-ROM called WHO BUILT AMERICA? is now available for Windows. Widely praised by educators and critics alike,  and <b>george jr. </b>likes it, too, WHO BUILT AMERICA? combines an award-winning American history text with an unparalleled collection of primary source materials. WHO BUILT AMERICA? for Windows is now available for about $49.95.
<P>

 <IMG SRC="weights1.jpg" WIDTH=270 HEIGHT=193 border=0 ALT=""align=right>


   WHO BUILT AMERICA? is a groundbreaking and superbly researched multimedia exploration of American history from 1876 to 1914. American Social History Project historians Roy Rosenzweig, Steve Brier, Josh Brown, and their colleagues have hand-crafted an interactive guide that takes the reader behind the printed page and back in time into the lives of the ordinary men and women who built America. This crucial period of industrial and urban growth, immigration, labor unrest, political conflict, and reform is brought to life through film clips, music, images, and extensive printed
material.
<p>
   WHO BUILT AMERICA? includes more than four and a half hours of audio (oral history, actuality sound, and music), forty-five minutes of archival film, over five thousand pages of historical documents, and more than seven hundred pictures, as well as dozens of graphs, maps, and many other features.

<p><hr width=75%><P>
 <IMG SRC="weights2.jpg" WIDTH=270 HEIGHT=201 border=0 ALT=""align=right>

<b>Hey, Break This</b>
    Another goodie we like is Grolier's 1966 GUINESS MULTIMEDIA DISC OF RECORDS, which presents some 15,000 - we counted - challenging feats ever performed by humans, as well as popular cultural stats, animal antics and the natural wonders of the world.
<p>
   This baby uses video sequences, photos and animation to help users experience the record-breaking moments. Based on what we've seen, we're picking the razor-tooth piranha as the team critter. Cost is about $15.95.

<p><hr width=75%><P>
<b>Comic Book 'Confidential' No More</b>
   Ron Mann's hip, funny, and highly acclaimed documentary gives comic books the respect they have long deserved in this second cool Voyager CD-Rom ($49.95). The only comprehensive documentary of comics and their creators ever made, COMIC BOOK CONFIDENTIAL combines interviews, historical footage, animations, and montages of comic art to produce a thoroughly entertaining account of the history of comics. 
<p>
The CD-ROM presents the film along with more than 100 pages of comics art, introductions and biographies of each artist, and a bibliography of their published works. Featured artists include Stan Lee, R. Crumb, Sue Coe, Art Spiegelman, Lynda Barry, Jack Kirby, and William Gaines.

<P>

<HR><BR>

<a href="/september/departments.html"><IMG SRC="/graphics/gotod.gif" WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=34 BORDER=0 align=left></a>

<A HREF="index.html"><IMG SRC="/graphics/home.gif" WIDTH=133 HEIGHT=34 border=0 align=right></A>
