<title>george jr. / october 1996 / departments / weights & measures</title>

</head>

<body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" LINK="#2F4F2F" VLINK="#c0c0c0" ALINK="#c0c0c0">

<a href="/october/departments.html"><IMG SRC="/graphics/gotod.gif" WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=34 BORDER=0 align=left></a>

<A HREF="index.html"><IMG SRC="/graphics/home.gif" WIDTH=133 HEIGHT=34 border=0 align=right></A>

<br clear=all>

<hr>

<br>

<H2>weights & measures</H2>

<blockquote>
<H2>1</H2>
Folk tales in which women<B> masquerade</B> as men:<I> A Riddle for a King, Across  the Sunlit Courtyard, Secure at Last, Rubies for a dog, The Legend of  Mary Ambree; The Mouse, the Thing and the Wand; The Sand-Sifter; A Tortuous Path; A Gown of Moontheads; What Will Be Will Be; The Coward and  the Heroine, A Matter of Honor.</I>
<H2>2</H2>
Among Americans aged 15 to 34, the homicide <B>death rate</B> increased by 50  percent between 1985 and 1991, from 13.4 deaths per 100,000 to 20.1.
<H2>3</H2>
First-TV, CMP Media's new Internet-only,  24-hour network, which debuted with Fresh Click: Life  Online, features a mix of Internet-related news, reports  about online games and a look at the personalities of the people who are making their mark on the Web. <B>Web site's actual weight</B>: 12 lbs, 6 oz.
<H2>4 </H2>
Year of origins of several fruits:
<B>Cantaloupe</B>: 2400 B.C., Iran
<B>Mandarin Orange</B>: 220 B.C., China
<B>Mango</B>: 16th century, Southeast Asia
<H2>5</H2>
A Web survey by Commerce Net and Nielson shows that 22-24% of people 16 years of age or older in the United States and Canada are on <B>the Internet</B>. The Internet market is widening to encompass the demographics of the general population. The survey also shows that Internet access in the United States and Canada rose 50% from August 1995 to April 1996.
<H2>6</H2>
At 9 p.m. Sept. 26,  the spokesperson for everyone who works in a cubicle, Scott Adams, creator of  the phenomenal comic strip<I> Dilbert</I>, made a<B> cameo</B> appearance on the  NBC sitcom<I> NewsRadio</I>.
<H2>7</H2>
Principal photography  is now underway for <I>The Lost World: Jurassic Park</I>,   by Steven  Spielberg and based on the best-selling <B>novel </B>by Michael Crichton. The film  is  the sequel to Jurassic Park, the highest-grossing motion picture of  all-time.<I> Jurassic Park</I> is the all time box office leader with worldwide ticket sales of more than $916 million since its release in 1993.
   The <B> film</B>  continued to break records when it was released on home video, where it holds the  title of top-selling live-action motion picture of all time. <I>The Lost World: Jurassic Park</I> is Steven Spielberg's first film since 1993, when he directed both<I> Jurassic Park </I>and <I>Schindler's List.</I>
<H2>8</H2>
Birth of the<B> bathtub</B>: Oct. 7, 1828 in England.
<H2>9</H2>
 <IMG SRC="duck.jpg" WIDTH=220 HEIGHT=166 border=0 ALT=""align=left>
<br>
<I>The National Audubon Society Interactive CD-ROM Guide to North American
Birds</I> has 2100 color photos of 723 species and 62 habitats,  bird calls for nearly 700 species,  texts culled from 13 birders' books,  700 maps and other stuff to make you <B>whoop and holler</B>, including Life lists (if you  have to ask, you don't want this cool CD-ROM from Knopf Multimedia).
<br clear=all>
<H2>10</H2>
Elise's <B>middle name</B> is Alexandra.
<H2>11</H2>
<I>Facets Complete Video Catalog No. 14</I>, distributed by Academy Chicago, is 520 pages long, with 600 illustrations. What's it about? 27,000 <B>movies </B>available on laser disk and video. Cost is $11.95. Call 312-751-7300.
<H2>12</H2>
On Oct. 12, a<B> par</B>tial <B>sol</B>ar <B>ecl</B>ipse will occur over Europe and northern Africa.
<H2>13</H2>
Following its Sept. 5  meeting in New York City, the Recording Industry Association of America's Board of Directors unanimously agreed to broaden its current<B> substance  abuse</B> initiatives to combat this problem at all levels of the industry.
     The initiative essentially continues long-standing internal label  efforts to provide rehab services for its artists and employees, and establishes a three-year $2 million grant to fund additional outreach  through the Musicians' Assistance Program. Of course, you'll be wanting some phone numbers:
<!-- List Tag --><UL>
<LI>Recording Industry Association of America -- Ellen Caldwell,  202-775-0101
<LI>Musicians' Assistance Program -- Buddy Arnold, 213-993-3197
<LI>BMG Entertainment -- Dennis Petroskey, 212-930-4961
<LI>EMI-Capitol Music Group North America -- Sue D'Agostino, 212-492-5440
<LI>MCA Music Entertainment Group -- Bob Bernstein, 818-777-0589
<LI>PolyGram Holding Inc. -- Dawn Bridges, 212-333-8357
<LI>Sony Music Entertainment -- Patricia Kiel, 212-833-4145
<LI>Warner Music Group -- Jim Noonan, 212-484-8840
</UL>
<H2>14</H2>
<I>The Beatles Anthology</I> project has resulted in the sale of 16 million copies of both <I>The Beatles Anthology Volume 1 and 2</I>.  Both sold record numbers upon their release -- Volume 1 was the <B> fastest-selling</B> double album ever (855,797 units in its first week) and Volume 2, released this past March, sold nearly 500,000 its first week.  Both made their debuts at  No. 1 on <I>Billboard</I>'s Top 200 Album Chart.
<H2>15</H2>
The American Medical Association released results of a national survey that indicated 75% of parents are <B>disgusted</B> with media violence, and that parents overwhelmingly want a stronger, more effective rating system  for movies, television shows, computer games and music.

</blockquote>
