<html>
<head>
<title>george jr. / november 1996 / features / opening gambit</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" LINK="#2F4F2F" VLINK="#c0c0c0" ALINK="#c0c0c0">
<a href="/november/features.html"><IMG SRC="/graphics/gotof.gif" WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=34 BORDER=0 align=left></a>
<A HREF="index.html"><IMG SRC="/graphics/home.gif" WIDTH=133 HEIGHT=34 border=0 align=right></A>
<br clear=all>
<hr>
<br>
<img src="/graphics/gambit.gif" width=150 height=100 ALIGN=left HSPACE=15 VSPACE=15 ALT="">
<br>

<B>The intro:</B>
<P></P>  Welcome to the November issue of<B> george jr.</B>, the internet monthly that dogs and kestrals hear zipping through the modem long before any other kind of sentient being even can hear a <a href="whistle.html">whistle</a>.
<P></P>Once again, we bring you an international jamboree of writing talent, book talk, split hairs, curious links and digitized comfort. We are not any Tom, Dick or any other George; we are only this one, because our vastly different DNAs deem it so.
<P></P>This month, we includes Q&As with Chinese painter and writer <B>Belle Yang</B>, mystery writer<B> Robert Crais</B> and futurist <B>James Halperin.</B> Just after Halperin's Q&A, you'll note an alluringly named link called <B>Everything's Future</B>. This, dear reader, is Halperin's time line of our future. Stand back and hold hands with your friends, because it's going to get a little rough.
<P></P><B>Stanley Crawford</B> is back with us again, offering bold advice to his loved ones; and <B>Ask Kitty</B> has some oblique responses for, we presume, <b>george jr</b>.'s readers, who sure do love the email button. <B>Oliver North</B>'s secret e-mails get no prettier in our <b>White House E-mail</b> department, so we offer a fresh selection of them each Sunday.  Filing two more reports from literature's front lines, Ace Correspondent <B>Nicholas A. Basbanes</B> this November writes about novelists <B>William Kennedy</B> and uni-namer <B>Sapphire</B>.
<p>
November's cover art is <b>Guy Davenport</b>'s acrylic "Ford, Joyce, 
Pound and Quinn," one of dozens of Davenport's paintings and drawings 
reproduced in  Eric Anderson Reece's fascinating book about Davenport's 
splendid artwork, <i>A Balance of Quinces</i> (copyright 1996 by Guy 
Davenport, and reproduced in <b>george jr.</b> courtesy of Reece and 
Davenport's publisher, New Directions). 

<P></P> Apart from some <a href="sarcasm.html">very mild sarcasm</a>  every now and then, <b>george jr.</b> has nothing to feel uneasy about, though the citizenry does. With them - i.e., you - in mind, we've given over<B> the uneasy chair </B>to Pulitzer Prize winner <b>James MacGregor Burns.</b>
<P></P>Because sentiment and nostalgia sets in  at  the most unlikely of hours, we offer the item called<B> Mania</B>, which you'll clock to  soon enough. Likewise, Sources. Enjoy.
<P>You have their numbers and you have<A HREF="http://www.coil.com/~gmyers/"> mine</A>. Don't forget to call me, Ishmael.
<P></P>
<B>The outro:</B>
<P></P>We thank you for your cards and letters, and herewith answer, as succinctly as possible, the longstanding question as to the identity of  team <B>george jr.</B>:
<UL>
<LI>Wing commander: <A HREF="MAILTO:gmyers@coil.com">George Myers Jr.</A>
<LI>Georgerator: <A HREF="MAILTO:ShellyMyers@georgejr.com">Shelly Myers</A>
<LI>Cameo:<A HREF="MAILTO:Lisee@georgejr.com"> Elise Alexandra Myers</A>
<LI>Providential provider:<A HREF="http://www.columbuspages.com/">ColumbusPages </A>
<LI>Director of Uploads & Gizmonics:<A HREF="MAILTO:dnewman@equity.net">Daniel Newman</A>, Doctor of Downloadology
<LI>The President of the U.S.: <A HREF="MAILTO: president@whitehouse.gov "> Still Mr. Clinton</A>
<LI>Stolen from Dentist Office: <A HREF="http://www.salon1999.com/">Salon</A>, <A HREF="http://www.bid.com/coffeejrnl/">Coffee Journal</A>,   <A HREF="http://www.britannia.com/">Britannia</A>.
<LI>NASDAQ: geojun (up 43)
<LI>Personal mythologies:<A HREF="http://ourworld.compuserve.com/homepages/agamemnon/Myths.htm"> Imagos,</A> everywhere
