<H2>poem by george myers jr</H2> 


<BR>
<BR>
<B><CENTER>
anorexia
</B></CENTER><BR>

<pre>
<CENTER>
This
little
idea
spent
all
day
losing
weight
<B>.</B>
</CENTER>
</pre>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<!-- Horizontal Line Tag --><HR>
<B>George Myers Jr.</B> is the author of<I> Worlds Without End, Natural 
History, An Introduction to Modern Times </I>and <I>Alphabets 
Sublime</I>. His writings about literature and art have appeared in 
dozens of magazines around the country and abroad.


