<html>
<head>
<title>george jr. / november 1996 / departments / ask kitty</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" LINK="#2F4F2F" VLINK="#c0c0c0" ALINK="#c0c0c0">
<a href="/november/departments.html"><IMG SRC="/graphics/gotod.gif" WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=34 BORDER=0 align=left></a>
<A HREF="index.html"><IMG SRC="/graphics/home.gif" WIDTH=133 HEIGHT=34 border=0 align=right></A>
<br clear=all>
<hr>
<br>
<IMG SRC="/graphics/kitty.jpg" WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=214 ALIGN=RIGHT HSPACE=15>
<H2>Ask Kitty</H2>
<br>
  Cats are the most curious of sentient beings, who mostly care not a whit what we might think of them. Hence, they make the most excellent of advisors, even when answering our most dire of questions - as dear Kitty oddly does this time around - with seemingly oblique answers. Have a question?  (<B>george jr.</B> does, namely: What is she up to?) Ask <!-- MailTo Tag --><A HREF="MAILTO:kitty@georgejr.com">Kitty</A>.

<br clear=all>
<hr width=80%>
  
<p>

<blockquote>

<font size=+3>q.</font> My girlfriend seems to like me well enough, but she'll dance with any guy who comes along. What's the deal?
<br>
<font size=+3>a.</font>  "It is the nature of cats to do a certain amount of unescorted roaming." - <B>Adlai Stevenson</B>
<p>

<font size=+3>q.</font> I need the money but hate my job and would like to quit and start something new. Do you advise against it?
<BR>
<font size=+3>a.</font> "What is the victory of a cat on a hot tin roof? ... Just staying on it,  I guess, as long as she can." - <B>Tennessee Williams</B>
<p>

<font size=+3>q.</font> My boss acts neither vulnerable or impervious, like none of the rest of us are here. Is he the Buddha, or what?
<BR>
<font size=+3>a.</font> "Cats, no less liquid than their shadows, offer no angles to the wind.  They slip, diminished, neat, through loopholes less than themselves." 
- <B>S.F. Tessimond</B>
<p>

<font size=+3>q.</font> I'm living with a guy who refuses to clean up after himself. Like I want to marry this Mess-o-potamia. Do I dump him, or do you think he'll change, given time?
<BR>
<font size=+3>a.</font> "The wildcat is the 'real' cat, the soul of the domestic cat; unknowable  to human beings, he yet exits inside our household pets, who have long  ago seduced us with their seemingly civilized ways." - <B>Joyce Carol Oates</B>
<p>

<font size=+3>q.</font> My wife seems jolted into limbo ever time she opens up a Chinese menu. 'Too many choices,' she says, 30 minutes after looking it over. How can I hurry her without annoying her?
<br><font size=+3>a.</font> "Most cats, when they are Out want to be In, and vice versa, and often  simultaneously." - <B>Louis J. Camuti, D.V.M.</B>
</blockquote>

<p>
<HR><BR>
<a href="/november/departments.html"><IMG SRC="/graphics/gotod.gif" WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=34 BORDER=0 align=left></a>
<A HREF="index.html"><IMG SRC="/graphics/home.gif" WIDTH=133 HEIGHT=34 border=0 align=right></A>
</BODY>
