<head>

<title>george jr. / november 1996 / departments / national public rodeo (week 1)</title>

</head>

<body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" LINK="#2F4F2F" VLINK="#c0c0c0" ALINK="#c0c0c0">

<a href="/november/departments.html"><IMG SRC="/graphics/gotod.gif" WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=34 BORDER=0 align=left></a>

<A HREF="index.html"><IMG SRC="/graphics/home.gif" WIDTH=133 HEIGHT=34 border=0 align=right></A>

<br clear=all>

<hr>

<br>

<IMG SRC="/graphics/rodeo.gif" WIDTH=185 HEIGHT=132 ALIGN=left HSPACE=15 VSPACE=30>
<br><br>

 <I>  Independence Day</I>, the $286- million-plus box-office champion and fastest grossing movie of all time, is set to attack more than 100,000 retail outlets on video across North  America
November 22.  
   

<P></P>

The highly anticipated  video  release of the year's biggest and most popular film will be made available to  the largest consumer video purchasing base ever at ownable  price  of $22.98  in the U.S. and $24.98 in Canada. For a limited time  only  and while supplies last, <I>Independence Day</I> will be available with free,  exclusive 3D Live Action Art, the most spectacular and collectible package and gift  with purchase ever created for a video release.
  

<P> </P>

   Still wowing enthusiastic theater-goers across North America,  <I>Independence Day </I> rewrote the record books for every major box-office  milestone. It is the fastest film in history to ever reach the $100 million  mark  (7 days), the $150 million mark (12 days) and the $200 million mark (21 days). On its way it also captured the box-office records for highest single  day gross, biggest opening weekend gross, biggest three-day gross and  biggest
five-day gross. 

<P></P>

On its way to a gross of over $300 million ($286  million  to date) at the box office, it currently ranks as the No. 6 film of all time. The www.ID4.com has become the most-visited film website of all time,  totaling more than 75 million "hits" since its inception.
<!-- Horizontal Line Tag --><HR>
<B>Opening the Doors again
</B>
   

<P></P>

 Graphix Zone  will release <I>The Doors</I> CO-ROM, bringing the music, the magic, and the history of J.M. and the band. With two founding members graduates of the UCLA Film School, it was
inevitable that The Doors' original mix of jazz, California-surf flamenco guitar and Chicago blues would explode into a primordial mix of drama and music that is just as relevant today as it was nearly three  decades  ago. 

<P></P>

 In 1993, when they were inducted into the Rock n' Roll Hall of Fame, the surviving members of The Doors once again brought the house down with  a  live Jam of Doors classics <I>Break On Through, Light My Fire</I> and  <I>Roadhouse Blues </I>featuring Pearl Jam's Eddie Vedder on vocals.
<!-- Horizontal Line Tag --><HR>


<B>Party time, again</B>

   <I>Party of Five</I>, the  companion soundtrack to the series of the same  name  on FOX, will be released this week by Reprise Records.  A combination of songs exclusive to the show, new releases from artists and  <I>Party of Five</I> season favorites, the soundtrack features  cuts from the Bodeans, Big Bad Voodoo Daddy, BT with Tori Amos, Chaka Khan  with Bruce Hornsby, Holly Palmer, Joe Jackson, Laurie Sargent, Nanci Griffith, Rickie Lee Jones, Howard Jones, Rusted Root, Shawn Colvin, Stevie Nicks  and Syd Straw.
      <I>Party of Five</I>, which was the winner of the 1996 Golden Globe Award  For Best Drama Series, explores the lives of the five Salinger brothers and sisters determined to stay together following the tragic loss of their parents. The one-hour drama from Columbia Pictures Television focuses  on  the way the family uses the creativity, humor and love instilled by their  parents
to deal with the conflicts and demands of what we in the business of everyday life call everyday life.
   <!-- Horizontal Line Tag --><HR>

     
    <B> King David gets contract at last
</B>
     

<P></P>

  Alan Menken and Tim Rice's <I>KING DAVID </I>will open the historic, newly renovated New Amsterdam Theatre, it was announced today by Michael D. Eisner, chairman and CEO and Michael S.  Ovitz, president of The Walt Disney Company. <I>KING DAVID</I> will be a  world  premiere concert event based on the story of the shepherd boy who was chosen to be  king of Israel and is being produced by Walt Disney Theatrical Productions  in association with Andre Djaoui. Performances of KING DAVID will begin  on  May 20, 1997 and run through May 24, 1997 for five performances only.
    

<P></P>

 "King David is a hero for all time whose life is one of history's  greatest stories," said Eisner. "Alan Menken and Tim Rice have been  key  creative forces behind six of our most successful productions, and we are excited to  be working with them again.  We also look forward to working with noted producer Andre Djaoui."
  

<P></P>

   Eisner said the world premiere concert event is the first step toward a possible "theatricalization" of KING DAVID.  "Three of Tim Rice's earlier works, 'Chess,' 'Evita' and 'Jesus Christ Superstar,' were performed as concert events before they were expanded into full scale musicals,"  Eisner noted. 
    

<P></P>

 This production of KING DAVID will mark the third time that Menken  and Rice have been a composer/lyricist team on a Disney  production.  Previously, they collaborated to expand the score for the stage version of the 1994 Tony(R) Award winning "Beauty and the Beast."  Likewise, they wrote three songs together for the blockbuster hit "Aladdin" including "A Whole New  World"
for which they received an Academy(R) Award.
   

<P></P>

  "The New Amsterdam Theatre has been called the 'crown jewel' of  Broadway and we are pleased to rededicate this legendary theatre with a dynamic  new work by Alan Menken and Tim Rice," said Ovitz. Plans are underway  for  a live cast recording of this world premiere concert event to be released later in the year."
    <!-- Horizontal Line Tag --><HR>


<B>     @Home @work</B>




<P></P>



<P></P>

At Home Corporation (@Home), a pioneering provider of high-speed, interactive services  via  cable infrastructure, has announced a series of relationships with an impressive list of companies in television, print media and Web  programming.  These companies, who are participants in @Home's Media Development Program , are given access to tools and technologies that will enable them to offer  a wide variety of new cable Internet services ranging from interactive video  to stock and sports tickers to robust online shopping. To date,  sixty  companies have joined the program, and more are being added daily.
   

<P></P>

  @Home Network connects personal computer users to the Internet  using high-speed cable modems and its proprietary network.  The cable connection provides users significant increases in speed over conventional  Internet access, and @Home's network allows for unique content offerings that go beyond current Web experiences.
<!-- Horizontal Line Tag --><HR>

<B>Sauter and Paymar packs new paunch</B>
 

<P></P>

 <I> INSIDE EDITION </I>and <I>AMERICAN JOURNAL</I> Investigative Units  have added award-winning  reporters Jim Paymar and Mark Sauter.
   

<P></P>

  Sauter, a two-time Emmy-winner and long a mainstay of the <I>AMERICAN JOURNAL</I> staff has moved to <I>INSIDE EDITION</I> for the 1996-97 season.  Although  primarily an investigative reporter, Sauter also handles breaking news and provided <I>AMERICAN JOURNAL</I>'s on-scene coverage of the crash of TWA Flight 800.
   

<P></P>

  Paymar, a four-time Emmy-winner who also covered the TWA crash and produced a series of exclusives on the O.J. Simpson case for <I>AMERICAN  JOURNAL</I> last season, now moves into the show's investigative unit.  Before joining <I>AMERICAN JOURNAL</I>, Paymar was a correspondent and anchor of "News 4 New  York." 
<!-- Horizontal Line Tag --><HR>

<B>
Record entries for big whoop</B>

  

<P></P>

   A record-breaking 2,260 entries have been submitted for the 18th Annual CableACE Awards, the cable  industry's highest programming honor, recognizing excellence in original  programming
achievement.
     

<P></P>

The black-tie ceremony will take place November 16 from  the Wiltern Theater, airing exclusively on Turner Network Television (TNT) from 9:00-11:00 PM/ET. Drew Carey, star of the ABC comedy snore, <I>The  Drew  Carey Show</I>, will host the telecast produced by Tall Pony Productions.  Tony Eaton will executive produce; Ron de Moraes directs.
   <!-- Horizontal Line Tag --><HR>

       <B>
     Melvin Van Peebles holding</B>

  

<P> </P>

  The Melvin Van Peebles Film Festival scheduled to begin August 7 and run through Sunday, August 11, 1996, somewhere in America, if not anywhere, is being rescheduled for February 1997 to coincide with Black History Month. For more information, contact the Festival office, 213-427-5939. 


<P><hr width=75%><P>

<b>See you next Sunday.</b>
