<IMG SRC="/graphics/rodeo.gif" WIDTH=185 HEIGHT=132 ALIGN=left HSPACE=15 VSPACE=30>
<br><br>

<B>
Talentless actor runs for 'Daylight'</B>

    <P></P><I>Daylight,</I>  Universal Pictures' suspenseful action-drama starring Sylvester Stallone, will open nationwide  December 6. The release of <I>Daylight</I>,  Stallone's  31st motion picture, coincides with the 20th anniversary of the blockbuster film that first catapulted the actor to international superstardom, the  Academy Award-winning <I>Rocky</I>. As if.
  <P></P>  In<I> Daylight</I>, a devastating accidental explosion traps a small group of people in the Manhattan Tunnel, an underwater commuter roadway linking  New York City with New Jersey.  As more and more sections of the tunnel collapse behind and in front of them, the survivors - ordinary citizens from all  walks of life - come to the terrifying realization that they may die at any  moment by suffocation, drowning or fire.   As if. 
   <P></P>The only hope rests with Kit Latura
(Sylvester Stallone), an ex-Emergency Medical Services chief, who risks his life in a harrowing journey through the tunnel's unstable ventilation system in order to reach them.  As if. But once inside the tunnel, Kit becomes  trapped  with them, and he begins a race against time and the elements as he improvises a roller-coaster ride of escape to lead the group back to daylight. As if.
<!-- Horizontal Line Tag --><HR>


<b>Smashing Pumpkins</b>

    <P></P>The Smashing Pumpkins'  "The Aeroplane Flies High," a special 5-CD singles box set, lands in stores  across the country on November 19th from  Virgin Records.
  <P></P>    Packaged in a custom made "retro" style 45-rpm carrying case, the set contains all 5 released singles from the "Mellon Collie and the Infinite Sadness" album ("Bullet with Butterfly Wings," "1979," "Zero," "Tonight ' Tonight," and "Thirty-Three") as well as all corresponding B-sides, which  in some cases have only been available on import.
  <P></P>    As a special bonus, 5 previously unreleased cover songs are added to  the "Bullet with Butterfly Wings" CD: "You're All I've Got Tonight" (The Cars); "Destination Unknown" (Missing Persons); "Dreaming" (Blondie); "A Night  Like This" (The Cure); and "Clones (We're All)" (Alice Cooper).
<hr>
<B>Aretha Franklin:  Queen still reigns</B>

 <P></P>   In an appearance at New York City's Carnegie Hall, Aretha Franklin was awarded a platinum album by  Arista Records President Clive Davis for the Aretha Franklin Greatest Hits  package.
<P></P>The JVC Jazz Festival performance given by  Franklin was touted by journalists as being the best of the series.  The Queen played and sang at the piano, thrilled the audience and proved she has still got the stuff to keep her in demand curtain call after curtain call - album after album.
  <P></P>   The Queen is readying for her ninth Arista records release this month, as well as a cooking video affectionately called <I>Switchin' in the Kitchen with Aretha</I> and an autobiography penned by David Ritz.
<BR>
<!-- Horizontal Line Tag --><HR>

<B>Heroes sold out, big shock</B>

<P></P>The  re-launch of  the world's greatest super heroes took hold last month when the  first of Marvel Comics Heroes Reborn series became available nationwide.<I> Fantastic Four No. 1 </I>is the first issue in this series of new incarnations  of Marvel Comics' classic titles<I> Captain America, The Fantastic Four, Iron  Man </I>and <I>The Avengers.</I>
   <P></P>  Heroes Reborn will present new No. 1 issues and feature new origin  stories for all four titles. Captain America, The Fantastic Four, Iron Man  and  The Avengers will be revamped, with modern concerns and sensibilities and  more prepared to face the challenges of the '90s. The   re-launch  was preceded by a summer-long storyline focusing on the battle and defeat of genuinely bad person Onslaught, which involved every title in the Marvel universe and quite a few marketing geniuses besides.
<!-- Horizontal Line Tag --><HR>

 <B>Keaton engaged</B>
   <P></P>  ENGAGE  Games  Online entered into an  online  content  deal  with Digital Alchemy, a  multimedia  production  company  created  by  former CNN bureau chief Chip Walter and actor  Michael  Keaton  to  develop  broad-appeal
lifestyle interactive content. 
<P></P>The first  product  to  come  out  of  this relationship will be Human Beans, the  world's  first  virtual  coffee  house - one that is rich with  personable  characters,  amusing  games,  fascinating trivia and a fine brew of information about the world's most popular addiction, coffee. ENGAGE Games Online will launch its  new  multi-player  games and entertainment service later this summer  on  America  Online  and  Prodigy.  The  ENGAGE web site can be accessed at <!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="http://www.gamesonline.com./">www.gamesonline.com.</A>
  <!-- Horizontal Line Tag --><HR>

   <B>  SJS Entertainment secured  for broadcast
</B>
     <P></P>Asylum Recording star Bryan White held a free performance and benefit radiothon at the  Oklahoma Opry in Oklahoma City  on September 30. White performed for the families of Oklahoma City's bombing victims at this  invitation-only event. All  proceeds  from the radiothon, which will include the live broadcast of White's  performance, benefit the Federal Employee Education and Assistance Fund aiding children injured or left without parents because of the Oklahoma City  bombing last year.
   <!-- Horizontal Line Tag --><HR>

    

 <B>Melnick joins Buzz</B>
  
   <P></P> Shuttle astronaut  Bruce Melnick has been named technical consultant for the action-packed  drama <I>The Cape</I>, MTM Entertainment's new series for first-run syndication. Melnick joins astronaut Buzz Aldrin,  who  also serves as technical consultant on the series. The Cape is a weekly  hour- long drama illuminating the exhilarating lifestyle of American astronauts and astronaut candidates.
    <!-- Horizontal Line Tag --><HR>

<B>
   DEVO in the 'Smart Patrol'
</B>
   <P></P> Discovery Records  released the audio CD version of <I>DEVO Presents Adventures Of The Smart Patrol</I>, the audio soundtrack companion piece to the INSCAPE CD-ROM  game written and directed by DEVO's Gerald V. Casale, and featuring new and old music from DEVO. The CD-ROM game is a surrealistic social satire  created  by Casale and DEVO Mark Mothersbaugh, founders and principal songwriters of  DEVO, progenitors of American post-industrial techno-pop.
     

<P><hr width=75%><P>

<b>See you next Sunday.</b>
