JOHN M. POINDEXTER

NOTE FROM: Stephen Farrar
SUBJECT: Replenishment of the International Development 
Association (IDA)
Treasury is preparing for a July 15 international meeting to discuss a 
multiyear replenishment of IDA (the soft-loan arm of the World 
Bank). There will be pressure to commit to a U.S. pledge. While such 
a pledge could be made within Treasury's out-year budget planning 
ceilings included in the FY87 Budget, recent congressional cuts make 
those ceilings unrealistic.

State is preparing Shultz to ask Baker--probablt at next Tuesday's 
economic breakfast--to avoid an IDA pledge until the Administration's 
budget priorities can be agreed upon based on work of the newly 
created SIG. I told State staff that I thought you would support that 
position.

