<title>george jr. / december 1996 / features / trout fishing in america
</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" LINK="#2F4F2F" VLINK="#c0c0c0"
ALINK="#c0c0c0">
<a href="/december/arcadia.html"><IMG SRC="/graphics/gotoa.gif" WIDTH=150
HEIGHT=34 BORDER=0 align=left></a>
<A HREF="index.html"><IMG SRC="/graphics/home.gif" WIDTH=133 HEIGHT=34
border=0 align=right></A>
<br clear=all>
<hr>
<br>
<H2>recipe:</H2> 
<h3>george jr.'s trout fishing in america </h3>

<P>


<br clear=all>

<blockquote>





<b>G</b>et yourself two medium (8 ounces each) trout fillets, skin on.<br>

1 tablespoon of vegetable oil<br>


2 tablespoons plus 2 teaspoons of unsalted butter<br>


3 large shallots, minced<br>


1 bottle of champagne<br>


Salt and ground paper to taste.<br>

<hr>


<b>O</b>n a hot skillet, place the fish skin-side down. Cook for 2-3 minutes each side. Remove skin.   Pour in 1 cup of champagne and cook until reduced by half.
Transfer to side dish.  Add shallots and saute until translucent. Add salt, paper, and fish, and heat thoroughly... Eat 'em up.



</blockquote>

