<head>

<title>george jr. / december 1996 / departments / weights & measures</title>

</head>






<body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" LINK="#2F4F2F" VLINK="#c0c0c0" ALINK="#c0c0c0">

<a href="/december/departments.html"><IMG SRC="/graphics/gotod.gif" WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=34 BORDER=0 align=left></a>

<A HREF="index.html"><IMG SRC="/graphics/home.gif" WIDTH=133 HEIGHT=34 border=0 align=right></A>

<p>
<br>
<br clear=all>

<Br><br>
<blockquote><blockquote>
<H3>1.</H3>

<B>Breed of deadliest dogs and registered kills since 1990:</B>

<ul>
<LI>Pit Bull, 17.
<LI>German sheperd, 6.
<LI>Chow, 5.
<LI>Malamute, 5.
<LI>Husky, 4.
<LI>Wolf hybrid, 4.
<LI>Akita, 2.
<LI>Rottweiler, 2.
<LI>Doberman, 1.
<LI>Colleague, 324.<P>
</ul>

<H3>2.</H3>

<B>Most translated authors in the world (ranked):</B>
<ul>
<LI>V.I. Lenin
<LI>Agatha Christie
<LI>Jules Verne
<LI>William Shakespeare
<LI>Enid Blyton
<LI>Leo Tolstoy
<LI>Charles Perrault
<LI>Georges Simenon
<LI>Karl Marx
<LI>Fyodor Dostoevski<P>
</ul>

<H3>3.</H3>

<B>Crucified Saviors other than Jesus Christ:</B>
<ul>
<LI>Chrishna (India)
<LI>Sakia (Hindu)
<LI>Thamuz (Syria)
<LI>Wittoba (Telingonese)
<LI>Ieo (Nepal)
<LI>Hesus (Celtic Druid)
<LI>Quexalcote (Mexico)
<LI>Quirnus (Rome)
<LI>Prometheus (Greece)
<LI>Thulis (Egypt)
<LI>Indra (Tibet)
<LI>Alcestos (Greece)
<LI>Atys (Phrygia)
<LI>Crite (Chaldea)
<LI>Bali (Orissa)
<LI>Mithra (Persia)
</ul>



<H3>
4.</H3>
<blockquote>
<B>Epidemics and plagues in the U.S.
</B><br>
<B>1699</B>: Yellow Fever in Charleston and Philadelphia, 370 die.<br>

<B>1735-1740: </B>Diptheria epidemic in New England, 80 percent of the children die.<br>

<B>1793:</B> Yellow Fever in Philadelphia, 4,044 die.<br>

<B>1832:</B> Cholera epidemic in New York City; 4,000 die.<br>

<B>1863:</B> Yellow Fever in New Orleans; 7,848 die.<br>

<B>1861-1865: </B>Typhoid, 187,000 die.<br>

<B>1878:</B> Yellow Fever, New Orleans and Memphis; 14,000 die.<br>

<B>1900:</B> Bubonic plague in San Francisco, 117 dead.<br>

<B>1916:</B> Polio epidemic, 6,000 dead.<br>

<B>1931</B>: Diptheria epidemic; 17,000 dead.<br>

<B>1952:</B> Polio epidemic; 3,300 dead.<br>

<B>1980 - ?</B> AIDS epidemic, Worldwide, 22 million people are infected, 1 million of them children. 
Every day sees 8500 new infections, 1000 of them in children. 
 Each minute more than five people are newly infected with HIV. 


</blockquote>
</blockquote></blockquote>


