<html><head><title>george jr. / december 1996 / faq / Who george jr. is</title></head><body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" LINK="#2F4F2F" VLINK="#c0c0c0" ALINK="#c0c0c0"><a href="/december/departments.html"><IMG SRC="/graphics/gotof.gif" WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=34 BORDER=0 align=left></a><A HREF="index.html"><IMG SRC="/graphics/home.gif" WIDTH=133 HEIGHT=34 border=0 align=right></A><br clear=all><hr><br><H2>Who george jr. is</H2><blockquote><p align=left><br><b>george jr.</b> is George Myers Jr., books editor for The Columbus <a href="http://www.dispatch.com">Dispatch</a> (614-461-5265, if you must call me at work and, if you do, and if I'm on deadline, could you kindly make it quite brief).<p>  The content of <b>george jr.</b> is written by George Myers Jr., except where others' bylines appear and except for the p.r. stuff sent in by publicists for the various firms identified in  <a href="sources.html">Sources</a>, or other outfits that haven't yet appeared as Sources but who, shucks, nevertheless are.<p>   Anybody can have a magazine of her or his own. This is America, yes?</blockquote><P><HR><BR><a href="/december/departments.html"><IMG SRC="/graphics/gotof.gif" WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=34 BORDER=0 align=left></a><A HREF="index.html"><IMG SRC="../graphics/home.gif" WIDTH=133 HEIGHT=34 border=0 align=right></A></BODY></HTML>
</DOC>
