<br><br><br>
<H2><B>george jr.</B> is:</h2>
<br clear=all>
<br><br>
<!--List Tag--><UL>
<LI>A Magellan Four-Star Site
<a href=http://www.mckinley.com><img align=right src=magellan.gif></a>
<LI>An Internet Voyager Four-Star Site
<LI>A Yahoo! Best of the Web, Yahoo! Cool Site of the Day/Week
<LI>Praised by  PRN Radio Network
<li>"An electic, thoughtful literary zine that looks at topics outside the 
ordinary, <b>george jr.</b> is a good mark by which to judge all the 
rest." - <i>The Net,</i>  November 1996
<LI>And,  of course, much discussed in <I>Internet Underground</I>, The AP and UPI, <I>The Columbus Dispatch, American Journalism Review, Boston Globe, The Kansas City Star, The Patriot-News, The Manchester Guardian</I> (U.K.), <I>The Miami Herald</I>  and many others.</UL</a>
</ul>
<b>george jr.</b> is a "spiffy e-zine" that "spares no irony when it comes to subject matter ranging from the mineral hardness of American leaders (diamond: 10; Perot: 9) all the way to how your senator voted ('Sure. Yes. Undoubtedly. Whatever.') The site is pretty interesting, and offers a link to recently declassified White House e-mail, which is always full of tawdry little secrets." - Netsurfer Digest, April 30, 1996</a>

<br><HR>
<a href="/november/features.html"><IMG SRC="/graphics/gotof.gif" WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=34 BORDER=0 align=left></a>
<A HREF="index.html"><IMG SRC="/graphics/home.gif" WIDTH=133 HEIGHT=34 border=0 align=right></A>


</body>
