<head>
<title>george jr. / november 1996 / features / opening gambit</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000" LINK="#2F4F2F" VLINK="#c0c0c0" ALINK="#c0c0c0">
<a href="/november/features.html"><IMG SRC="/graphics/gotof.gif" WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=34 BORDER=0 align=left></a>
<A HREF="index.html"><IMG SRC="/graphics/home.gif" WIDTH=133 HEIGHT=34 border=0 align=right></A>
<br clear=all>
<hr>
<br>
<table align=left>
<tr><td><a href = gambit.html><img src="/graphics/gambit.gif" width=150 border=0 height=100 ALIGN=left HSPACE=15 VSPACE=15 ALT=""></a>
</td></tr>
<tr><td align=center>
<font size=-1><b><a href = gambit.html>back to opening gambit</b></a></font>
</td></tr>
</table>

<br>

<P></P><i>Je suis scandalise! </i>We are shocked to learn that Mary Engelbreit, the illustrator of dainty children clutching flowers, has launched a new magazine called <b>Mary Engelbreit's Home Companion</b> - in plain defiance of  the Prairie Home Companion empire, and other publications that use the word 'Home' bolder than a mastif on the plains of Ohio.
<P></P> Has this Engelbreit woman no idea of the trouble she'll fall into? And that superpowers are buying up, left and right, phrases such as "left and right," not no mention vowels, consonants and several gutteral sounds that heretofore were common to many of us?</a>

<br><HR>
<a href="/november/features.html"><IMG SRC="/graphics/gotof.gif" WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=34 BORDER=0 align=left></a>
<A HREF="index.html"><IMG SRC="/graphics/home.gif" WIDTH=133 HEIGHT=34 border=0 align=right></A>


</body>
