<body><body background="images/wavy.jpg">
<h2><center><img src="heading.jpg"><br><b>ABOUT TCCM Design</h2>
</center></b><img src="images/line.gif"><p>
TCCM Design was one of the Capital District New York's oldest web design
firms. The company was originally formed as a division of <a 
href="http://www.albany.net/~tricity/mast.html">Tri-City Computing 
Magazine</a>, when the magazine first went online in early 1994. After a 
couple of months of creating a monthly web version of our print  publication, TCCM
Design's staff began to offer their services to other businesses wanting 
to "get on the web".<p>

The company has grown quite well and continues to
expand every day. TCCM Design is no longer affiliated with Tri-City 
Computing 
Magazine and our offices are now located in the Southwestern U.S.. 
For a list of our clients please follow this link: <a 
href="biz.html">Client List</a><p>

Our staff includes web page design professionals, copy writers,
cgi, Java and Active X  programmers (for designing
those complicated forms and cool animations you might want for your site), 
graphic designers and research
consultants. All fully trained to assist you in taking your
business into the 21st century.<p>


Don't let your competition leave you standing in a cloud of their internet
marketing dust. Put your business
on what many call the greatest advertising opportunity since
television - the world wide web.<p>
Advertising on the web has the potential to reach approximately
25 million users world wide, 24 hours per day, 7 days per week<b> because 
the 
web never sleeps!</b> That's a lot of potential don't you think? 25 million 
consumers who may want to buy your product from the comfort of their own 
homes or offices.<p> Let TCCM Design help get you on the web; Linking your 
business to the world is
our business. Now and into the 21st Century, TCCM Design Web Services is 
your right choice.<p>

<p>

For more information just <a href="mailto:swcm@sprynet.com">email</a> 
us or fill out our <a href="form.html">information form</a> for a quote on 
setting up your own page on the web.<p>

<p>

<a href="http://www.tccmweb.com/index.html">Return to main
page</a><p>

<p>

<p>

<p>

<p>

 
</body>
