<HTML><body><BODY background="images/wavy.jpg">
<center><img src="heading.jpg"><h2>Welcome to our help page</h2><p></center>
<hr>
Here you'll find links to many helpful programs from web browsers to shareware sites. 
<P>
<h3>Web Related Sites</h3><p>
<a href="http://www.microsoft.com/ie/msie.htm">Microsoft Internet 
Explorer</a> Download the latest version of this very cool browser 
today.<p>
<a href="http://home.netscape.com/comprod/mirror/index.html">Netscape</a> 
Download the webs' most popular browser for FREE right here.<p>
<A HREF="http://www.awinc.com/cwsapps/">Stroud's Winsock Apps List</A>
If you own an IBM PC running windows and want one heck of a collection  of
shareware/freeware for use on the 'net, this is the place to go. If you own a Mac, or have enough
Windows Internet software, I'd say move on...
<P>
<a href= "http://mcia.com:80/ant/">The Ant</a> - HTML Conversion Utilities.<p>
<a href= "http://www.ncsa.uiuc.edu/SDG/Software/WinMosaic/General.html">Mosaic Web
Browser Site</a><p>
<a href= "/utils/windows/LVIEW31.ZIP">Download LView Image Viewer - 225K</a><p>
<a href= "http://www.ncsa.uiuc.edu/SDG/Software/WinMosaic/viewers.html">Site for other Web
Browser Viewer Software</a><p>
<a href= "http://www.trumpet.com.au/">Trumpet Winsock Site</a><p>
<a href= "/utils/windows/WS_PING.ZIP">Download WS_PING - Ping Utility for Windows -
60K</a><p>
<a href= "http://www.tucows.com">Ultimate Collection of Winsock Compliant Software</a><p>
<A 
HREF="http://www.macromedia.com">http://www.macromedia.com</A>Shockwave</a> Shockwave is a plug-in that allows Internet browsers to access
animations created with Macromedia Director. Since Director handles
both audio and visual effects, it provides an effective way to
advertise on the Internet. It also enables publishers to jazz up
their Web sites considerably. <p> 
<hr>
<h3>Windows Sharerware and Other Helpful Programs</h3><p>
<hr>
<A HREF="http://www.shareware.com">Shareware Com</A> (from
the folks at C|Net). A very nicely laid out site, but sometimes it's quite busy.
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.windows95.com/apps/nonapps.html">Windows 95 Magazine's
Non-network Shareware</A> Direct from Windows 95 magazine comes a collection of
shareware that's not (for once) related to the internet. Sorry, the files here are Win95 specific. 
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.hyperion.com/usox/index.html">The Used Software Exchange</A>
While nothing here is free, you can browse the aisles and shop for used software at incredibly low
prices. Since you're basically buying from other 'net users, you can haggle about price to your
heart's content.<p>
<a href= "http://www.computan.on.ca/~ksmith/collect.html">Collector's Showcase</a> -
Collector's Database SW</a>.<p>
<a href= "/utils/windows/WZ5a.exe">Download Winzip - Zip/Unzip Utility for Windows -
220K</a><p>
<A HREF="http://www.jumbo.com">http://www.jumbo.com</A></P>
I think this is the best shareware/freeware library in cyberspace.
Why? Jumbo's easy-to-use search tool helps you find what you need in
the nearly 50,000 files in categories such as business, education,
graphics, and games. A brief description of each file is included.
The files actually reside on servers around the world; Jumbo acts
like a giant switchboard to give you links to all the sites holding
the particular program. Select the site closest to you for the
speediest download.
<P><A HREF="http://www.windows95.com">http://www.windows95.com</A> Its selection of
freeware isn't quite as comprehensive as Jumbo's. Nevertheless, Windows95.com is worth a visit,
primarily for its innovative interface that includes Windows-style icons and a Taskbar.
<P><A HREF="http://wwwgalttech.com/index.shtml">http://wwwgalttech.com/index.shtml</A>
This site offers access to thousands of shareware programs. Like
Jumbo, it has a searchable database and lays out the programs in
various categories. It also features a top ten downl;oad section that
you can just click on and get the latest and hottest programs.
<P><A HREF="  http://www.msn.com">Microsoft</A> If you want free Microsoft software,
head to the company's Web site. The Windows software library is well organized, with a separate
section for downloading Microsoft Office macros, the Internet Explorer 2.0 and 3.0 Web
browser, utilities such as the Microsoft Word Technical Dictionary, and a self-running Microsoft
Office for Windows 95 demo. <p>
<A HREF="http://www.happypuppy.com">The Happypuppy.com</A> one of the best shareware
and software sites on the net today. Don't miss this one.<p>
<hr><a href="http://www.tccmweb.com/"><img src="images/vbs_bann.gif"></a><p>
<a href="http://www.tccmweb.com/index.html">Back to our main page</a><p>
