HREF="http://www.bath.ac.uk/~py3dlg/motorsport/chrislaw.htm">UK
Law At Christmas</A><DD><I>Summary</I>:  Eating a Christmas
dinner of more than three courses immediately puts you in
violation of a law passed by Oliver Cromwell's Long Parliament of
1646. The Holy Days and Fasting Days Act of 1551 makes it
obligatory for everyone to attend a church service on "the
Nativitie of our Lorde".<p>
